1
00:00:26,555 --> 00:00:27,584
(The business district for the first match)

2
00:00:27,585 --> 00:00:29,515
(Government Complex Sejong)

3
00:00:30,825 --> 00:00:32,184
(A business district targeting officer workers)

4
00:00:32,185 --> 00:00:33,324
(Estimated number of customers)

5
00:00:33,325 --> 00:00:34,455
(1,000 people)

6
00:00:35,825 --> 00:00:38,295
(A 1,000 dollar sales race)

7
00:00:38,395 --> 00:00:41,234
(Reach 1,000 dollars in sales as fast as possible.)

8
00:00:41,235 --> 00:00:43,665
(First-to-finish survival mission)

9
00:00:43,935 --> 00:00:46,734
(2 teams will be eliminated.)

10
00:00:46,735 --> 00:00:47,934
(2 teams will be shut down.)

11
00:00:47,935 --> 00:00:49,104
(However...)

12
00:00:49,105 --> 00:00:52,005
(The ingredient budget is limited to 300 dollars.)

13
00:00:52,545 --> 00:00:55,315
(Customers will not know whose restaurant they're ordering from.)

14
00:00:55,345 --> 00:00:58,515
(What kind of menu would sell in this area?)

15
00:00:58,945 --> 00:01:01,685
(That's for the customers to decide.)

16
00:01:04,855 --> 00:01:05,954
Will you add chilli oil?

17
00:01:05,955 --> 00:01:07,325
(Ma Restaurant)

18
00:01:12,395 --> 00:01:13,835
I think it needs more.

19
00:01:14,265 --> 00:01:15,964
Stir-fry this...

20
00:01:15,965 --> 00:01:18,064
and finish it on the spot.

21
00:01:18,065 --> 00:01:20,334
Add it later and quickly toss them together before serving.

22
00:01:20,335 --> 00:01:22,104
- Okay.
- Otherwise, the time isn't enough.

23
00:01:22,105 --> 00:01:24,405
- Okay.
- You can also add peperoncino.

24
00:01:25,045 --> 00:01:27,775
A difficult person?

25
00:01:28,275 --> 00:01:30,484
I've been labelled as a strict...

26
00:01:30,485 --> 00:01:31,915
or intimidating chef.

27
00:01:32,245 --> 00:01:36,255
Other chefs tend to be reserved around me.

28
00:01:37,025 --> 00:01:38,384
(During the opening ceremony)

29
00:01:38,385 --> 00:01:39,755
Chef Edward Kwon.

30
00:01:39,855 --> 00:01:41,825
(His lips get dry.)

31
00:01:42,455 --> 00:01:43,925
- Hello.
- Hello.

32
00:01:44,225 --> 00:01:46,364
- Hello. Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

33
00:01:46,365 --> 00:01:49,465
Chef Lim Ki Hak is here too.

34
00:01:50,865 --> 00:01:52,005
Oh, my.

35
00:01:54,935 --> 00:01:56,904
Chef Edward Kwon?

36
00:01:56,905 --> 00:01:59,074
I can't believe that he's here.

37
00:01:59,075 --> 00:02:00,775
He's also very strong.

38
00:02:01,515 --> 00:02:05,045
I'm a little scared to compete against him.

39
00:02:05,115 --> 00:02:06,415
He's the first person I'd be wary of.

40
00:02:07,615 --> 00:02:09,284
Hello, everyone. Nice to meet you.

41
00:02:09,285 --> 00:02:10,425
I'm Edward Kwon.

42
00:02:13,495 --> 00:02:14,625
I'm also here to learn.

43
00:02:15,255 --> 00:02:19,594
I was probably one of the youngest head chefs in a hotel in Korea.

44
00:02:19,595 --> 00:02:21,094
I don't even want to try this.

45
00:02:21,095 --> 00:02:24,104
I was the first one to be...

46
00:02:24,105 --> 00:02:26,104
on a chef survival show.

47
00:02:26,105 --> 00:02:27,105
(The first judge in Korean chef survival shows)

48
00:02:27,106 --> 00:02:30,774
I specialise in western food.

49
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:32,105
(He's built his career in western food on an international level.)

50
00:02:32,575 --> 00:02:36,245
I currently run a contemporary French restaurant...

51
00:02:36,785 --> 00:02:39,615
in Songjeong, Busan.

52
00:02:41,685 --> 00:02:43,924
I approach menu design...

53
00:02:43,925 --> 00:02:45,385
very professionally.

54
00:02:45,585 --> 00:02:49,295
I try to incorporate as many local products from Busan as possible.

55
00:02:50,195 --> 00:02:51,465
Ma Restaurant.

56
00:02:51,765 --> 00:02:53,294
We're both from Busan.

57
00:02:53,295 --> 00:02:55,664
We're chefs who came from Busan.

58
00:02:55,665 --> 00:02:56,665
(Ma Restaurant)

59
00:02:56,666 --> 00:02:59,464
Many people from Gyeongsang Province would understand.

60
00:02:59,465 --> 00:03:01,474
I thought that it'd be fun,

61
00:03:01,475 --> 00:03:03,105
so I named it Ma Restaurant.

62
00:03:04,275 --> 00:03:06,175
- Did you see the reaction?
- What?

63
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:10,385
When Chef Edward Kwon's menu was announced...

64
00:03:11,645 --> 00:03:12,745
Ma Restaurant.

65
00:03:13,315 --> 00:03:14,315
"Ma Restaurant?"

66
00:03:14,316 --> 00:03:15,384
What's Edward's menu?

67
00:03:15,385 --> 00:03:17,025
I'm curious about his too.

68
00:03:18,355 --> 00:03:21,155
What will Chef Edward Kwon make?

69
00:03:21,195 --> 00:03:22,755
It might overlap with ours.

70
00:03:24,865 --> 00:03:28,494
Kkanpunggi chicken stir-fried eggs over rice and spicy chilli shrimp.

71
00:03:28,495 --> 00:03:31,164
(Ingredient cost: 374.66 dollars)

72
00:03:31,165 --> 00:03:32,735
It's Chinese food.

73
00:03:33,405 --> 00:03:35,034
He picked Chinese cuisine.

74
00:03:35,035 --> 00:03:36,075
The combination seems perfect.

75
00:03:36,275 --> 00:03:37,705
This is quite shocking.

76
00:03:38,645 --> 00:03:39,874
Why did he pick Chinese cuisine?

77
00:03:39,875 --> 00:03:41,574
Isn't this Chinese cuisine?

78
00:03:41,575 --> 00:03:42,575
It's Chinese cuisine.

79
00:03:42,845 --> 00:03:44,285
He picked something Chinese.

80
00:03:44,985 --> 00:03:48,515
Many of the chefs seemed very shocked.

81
00:03:50,225 --> 00:03:51,425
But you know what?

82
00:03:52,055 --> 00:03:54,495
This is a completely different game.

83
00:03:54,955 --> 00:03:56,495
It's a business survival competition.

84
00:03:56,995 --> 00:04:00,295
You're evaluated by customers and the amount of sales.

85
00:04:00,335 --> 00:04:04,004
So the menu must be designed to win over customers.

86
00:04:04,005 --> 00:04:05,305
(The strategy is creating dishes that customers will choose.)

87
00:04:05,505 --> 00:04:08,135
You can be bold and sell a 300-dollar...

88
00:04:08,535 --> 00:04:09,835
course menu.

89
00:04:10,475 --> 00:04:12,874
I don't think this is possible for the first mission.

90
00:04:12,875 --> 00:04:13,944
You know why?

91
00:04:13,945 --> 00:04:16,944
Most office workers want a quick meal...

92
00:04:16,945 --> 00:04:19,385
and grab a coffee before heading back to work.

93
00:04:19,945 --> 00:04:24,525
In other words, my target is officer workers, civil servants,

94
00:04:24,955 --> 00:04:26,325
and men.

95
00:04:26,925 --> 00:04:29,454
Something delicious, affordable,

96
00:04:29,455 --> 00:04:30,965
- and fast.
- Right.

97
00:04:31,465 --> 00:04:32,495
Chinese food.

98
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:35,235
Kkanpunggi chicken over rice.

99
00:04:38,005 --> 00:04:39,005
And chilli shrimp.

100
00:04:40,505 --> 00:04:43,575
Kkanpunggi chicken over rice and chilli shrimp for 14.5 dollars

101
00:04:43,845 --> 00:04:46,305
Whether it's Korean, Japanese, or Chinese cuisine,

102
00:04:46,575 --> 00:04:47,575
you have to compete.

103
00:04:49,445 --> 00:04:50,445
In order to win.

104
00:04:51,415 --> 00:04:55,614
He's a friend and the head...

105
00:04:55,615 --> 00:04:59,254
of a Chinese kitchen at a well-known hotel in Busan.

106
00:04:59,255 --> 00:05:00,594
(Jeon Seok Su)

107
00:05:00,595 --> 00:05:03,595
When Chinese techniques are properly applied,

108
00:05:03,825 --> 00:05:06,865
it can strongly appeal to customers.

109
00:05:08,295 --> 00:05:11,264
Can you show off your Chinese cooking skills? It's been a while.

110
00:05:11,265 --> 00:05:13,105
Yes, sir. I will.

111
00:05:13,305 --> 00:05:15,834
The first certification I obtained was in Chinese cuisine.

112
00:05:15,835 --> 00:05:18,945
I can make most of the basic Chinese dishes.

113
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,745
(Starting with very simple egg fried rice)

114
00:05:23,785 --> 00:05:26,615
While stir-frying cold rice, I add eggs.

115
00:05:28,215 --> 00:05:31,425
The kick would be frying minced garlic...

116
00:05:32,185 --> 00:05:35,654
and using the infused oil to give a deep flavour.

117
00:05:35,655 --> 00:05:36,655
(Minced garlic oil)

118
00:05:36,925 --> 00:05:40,665
Salt, stir-fried sesame seeds, a bit of oyster sauce.

119
00:05:41,665 --> 00:05:44,205
The recipe is much simpler than you think.

120
00:05:45,565 --> 00:05:47,405
Beef radish soup would be nice,

121
00:05:48,105 --> 00:05:49,435
but we have no beef.

122
00:05:49,735 --> 00:05:51,975
So I'll make a clear broth using dried pollack...

123
00:05:52,045 --> 00:05:53,975
to give a refreshing taste.

124
00:05:56,045 --> 00:05:57,615
- Aren't you a French chef?
- What?

125
00:05:58,645 --> 00:06:00,855
I ran a Korean restaurant in Moscow a long time ago.

126
00:06:01,485 --> 00:06:02,615
I also ran one in Seoul.

127
00:06:03,315 --> 00:06:05,324
When you're abroad...

128
00:06:05,325 --> 00:06:06,685
and see Korean people...

129
00:06:07,555 --> 00:06:08,595
I'll fry the chicken.

130
00:06:13,325 --> 00:06:14,435
It's all done.

131
00:06:25,705 --> 00:06:28,844
(Next to Ma Restaurant is...)

132
00:06:28,845 --> 00:06:31,714
(a restaurant called Goal!)

133
00:06:31,715 --> 00:06:32,715
(Moaning)

134
00:06:33,599 --> 00:06:37,368
(Itaewon Prince, Hong Seok Cheon)

135
00:06:37,369 --> 00:06:40,638
The person I care about the least is Hong Seok Cheon.

136
00:06:40,639 --> 00:06:42,409
I don't even know why he's here.

137
00:06:42,609 --> 00:06:44,349
Is Hong Seok Cheon a chef?

138
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:48,978
Compared to professional chefs,

139
00:06:48,979 --> 00:06:51,449
a celebrity would be...

140
00:06:51,819 --> 00:06:55,219
(Team Goal! was labelled most frequently as the weakest.)

141
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:58,259
The one I noticed the most was...

142
00:06:58,529 --> 00:06:59,959
Seok Cheon.

143
00:07:00,159 --> 00:07:03,199
He's been in the restaurant business for a long time.

144
00:07:03,529 --> 00:07:06,938
Some might say, "He's not really a chef."

145
00:07:06,939 --> 00:07:09,339
But in terms of a business survival competition,

146
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:12,609
he carries out the intent of the show perfectly.

147
00:07:12,809 --> 00:07:13,879
Edward?

148
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:15,879
Is it Edward?

149
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:17,909
Why are you here?

150
00:07:18,949 --> 00:07:20,479
I came to see you.

151
00:07:21,219 --> 00:07:25,489
I thought it'd be fun with Edward, and he actually came.

152
00:07:26,149 --> 00:07:28,159
Here's what surprised me the most.

153
00:07:28,419 --> 00:07:32,759
Their fellow chefs who came on the show with them.

154
00:07:32,829 --> 00:07:33,928
Chef Park Min Hyuk.

155
00:07:33,929 --> 00:07:36,898
He and I worked together for a long time in Dubai.

156
00:07:36,899 --> 00:07:38,129
We also worked together in Korea.

157
00:07:38,369 --> 00:07:41,339
He's called Striker Chef on YouTube.

158
00:07:41,699 --> 00:07:42,768
My partner is...

159
00:07:42,769 --> 00:07:43,808
(Striker Chef, Park Min Hyuk)

160
00:07:43,809 --> 00:07:46,138
He's Edward Kwon's pupil.

161
00:07:46,139 --> 00:07:47,709
They've worked together.

162
00:07:47,979 --> 00:07:49,379
You know that Edward is here, right?

163
00:07:52,249 --> 00:07:54,149
Hello, I'm Park Min Hyuk.

164
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:57,619
I'm Striker Chef on YouTube.

165
00:07:57,949 --> 00:08:01,189
When I went abroad for the first time,

166
00:08:01,489 --> 00:08:03,689
he was the executive chef...

167
00:08:03,759 --> 00:08:04,959
at a seven-star hotel in Dubai.

168
00:08:05,989 --> 00:08:07,828
After that, we returned to Korea.

169
00:08:07,829 --> 00:08:09,299
The person I've worked with the longest.

170
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:11,299
In a way, I'm his right-hand man.

171
00:08:15,469 --> 00:08:17,339
- I wonder what Edward will sell.
- What?

172
00:08:17,839 --> 00:08:19,308
What if it overlaps with yours?

173
00:08:19,309 --> 00:08:20,309
No way.

174
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,679
- Isn't he your master?
- Yes.

175
00:08:21,739 --> 00:08:23,578
After separating ways,

176
00:08:23,579 --> 00:08:25,409
- we went into different things.
- Right.

177
00:08:25,649 --> 00:08:26,978
Edward's restaurant is next to ours.

178
00:08:26,979 --> 00:08:27,979
Really?

179
00:08:29,049 --> 00:08:30,818
- Right next to ours?
- I'm number 18,

180
00:08:30,819 --> 00:08:32,489
and Edward is number 17.

181
00:08:33,149 --> 00:08:34,819
- That's so fascinating.
- Isn't it funny?

182
00:08:34,859 --> 00:08:36,759
- What kind of twist of fate is it?
- I know.

183
00:08:37,959 --> 00:08:40,499
(The start of their twist of fate)

184
00:08:43,729 --> 00:08:46,369
(Choosing the spot next to Edward)

185
00:08:46,669 --> 00:08:49,998
My plan is to take away Edward's customers.

186
00:08:49,999 --> 00:08:51,938
- Really?
- We're right next to him.

187
00:08:51,939 --> 00:08:53,779
- Our restaurant is right next door.
- Yes.

188
00:08:54,609 --> 00:08:56,379
In a cooking battle,

189
00:08:56,739 --> 00:09:00,319
it's embarrassing to win easily in one go.

190
00:09:00,779 --> 00:09:02,819
You can't lose either.

191
00:09:04,019 --> 00:09:06,919
You know there are a lot of women among civil servants, right?

192
00:09:07,419 --> 00:09:08,959
We're targeting female customers.

193
00:09:09,159 --> 00:09:11,659
You definitely have a lot of experience,

194
00:09:11,729 --> 00:09:12,729
so it's strategic.

195
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:16,029
Somewhat pretty, light,

196
00:09:16,259 --> 00:09:18,329
and healthy food and names.

197
00:09:18,569 --> 00:09:19,969
- That sounds good.
- Healthy.

198
00:09:20,339 --> 00:09:22,339
He's been in the business for a long time.

199
00:09:22,569 --> 00:09:26,239
He truly understands what customers want.

200
00:09:26,439 --> 00:09:28,639
I will be supporting him...

201
00:09:29,209 --> 00:09:30,209
from behind.

202
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,709
This is our action plan for today.

203
00:09:32,179 --> 00:09:34,279
We need to put this up.

204
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:36,479
"Speed is the baseline."

205
00:09:36,719 --> 00:09:38,319
"We win with quality and execution."

206
00:09:38,449 --> 00:09:41,589
"Not a single plate is compromised in taste or presentation."

207
00:09:41,889 --> 00:09:44,759
Since the first time I worked with Edward,

208
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:47,359
he emphasized using paper.

209
00:09:47,599 --> 00:09:49,958
He likes people who know exactly what to do...

210
00:09:49,959 --> 00:09:51,569
at each stage.

211
00:09:51,969 --> 00:09:53,298
I hope that people will understand...

212
00:09:53,299 --> 00:09:54,739
- our menu.
- What?

213
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:56,738
I hope that they understand our menu.

214
00:09:56,739 --> 00:09:57,768
I know.

215
00:09:57,769 --> 00:09:59,139
Our signature dish is...

216
00:09:59,409 --> 00:10:02,709
Alaskan pink shrimp avocado tartare.

217
00:10:03,509 --> 00:10:05,148
The price is 16 dollars.

218
00:10:05,149 --> 00:10:06,479
(Alaskan pink shrimp avocado tartare, 16 dollars)

219
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:08,379
The key is...

220
00:10:09,219 --> 00:10:12,489
I take the leftover tail shells from the shrimp.

221
00:10:14,119 --> 00:10:16,519
I stir-fry them lightly to extract aroma.

222
00:10:19,459 --> 00:10:21,199
Gosh, that's lovely.

223
00:10:21,429 --> 00:10:22,558
It smells fragrant.

224
00:10:22,559 --> 00:10:23,568
(Handmade shrimp oil is complete.)

225
00:10:23,569 --> 00:10:24,569
Okay.

226
00:10:25,129 --> 00:10:26,828
(Gopchang laver)

227
00:10:26,829 --> 00:10:27,869
After that...

228
00:10:29,599 --> 00:10:31,008
Spray it once on both sides.

229
00:10:31,009 --> 00:10:32,069
Like this?

230
00:10:32,309 --> 00:10:35,809
After making the oil, we spray it on the laver.

231
00:10:36,179 --> 00:10:37,978
It's served wrapped in Gopchang laver.

232
00:10:37,979 --> 00:10:39,509
My hands feel hot.

233
00:10:39,549 --> 00:10:41,649
In a mixing bowl, I combine crisp stem lettuce,

234
00:10:42,079 --> 00:10:44,289
tangy sour cream, fried toast bread,

235
00:10:44,489 --> 00:10:45,989
and a bit of salt.

236
00:10:47,889 --> 00:10:49,619
I toss everything together...

237
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:55,099
and press it into a mold as a base on the plate.

238
00:10:56,559 --> 00:11:00,229
On top, I place avocado and Alaskan pink shrimp.

239
00:11:01,069 --> 00:11:02,898
- It looks so beautiful.
- What?

240
00:11:02,899 --> 00:11:03,939
It looks beautiful.

241
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:06,538
Let's plate it casually and let it fall into place.

242
00:11:06,539 --> 00:11:08,679
- Okay.
- Place it like this.

243
00:11:16,449 --> 00:11:19,149
When creating this dish, I had a clear idea in mind.

244
00:11:19,349 --> 00:11:22,319
This will definitely work if the customers are mostly women.

245
00:11:22,689 --> 00:11:26,059
(Hong Seok Cheon's restaurant targeting women and...)

246
00:11:26,429 --> 00:11:29,829
(Chef Edward Kwon's restaurant targeting men)

247
00:11:30,099 --> 00:11:33,169
From my perspective, mine is a lunch menu...

248
00:11:33,529 --> 00:11:36,699
that most men will choose.

249
00:11:37,209 --> 00:11:39,509
I just hope that...

250
00:11:39,769 --> 00:11:41,579
there won't be too many male customers.

251
00:11:43,209 --> 00:11:44,649
I'm very curious about...

252
00:11:45,179 --> 00:11:47,379
- what kind of customers we'll have.
- Right.

253
00:11:48,219 --> 00:11:52,089
(A neighbourhood battle between male and female target)

254
00:11:53,049 --> 00:11:54,388
(A red shop located next to them)

255
00:11:54,389 --> 00:11:55,688
I think we have a good chance.

256
00:11:55,689 --> 00:11:57,359
It won't be bad.

257
00:11:57,589 --> 00:11:59,789
The sauce is our priority.

258
00:12:00,129 --> 00:12:02,799
We need to make the stock after boiling the XO sauce.

259
00:12:02,899 --> 00:12:04,129
- In here?
- Yes.

260
00:12:07,439 --> 00:12:10,238
Hello, I'm the head chef at Deepin.

261
00:12:10,239 --> 00:12:11,338
I'm Choi Sang Hyun.

262
00:12:11,339 --> 00:12:13,039
(Chef and owner of Deepin, a wine dining restaurant)

263
00:12:13,839 --> 00:12:15,708
Deepin Sindang has...

264
00:12:15,709 --> 00:12:18,949
a Japanese-French inspired food and wine bar.

265
00:12:19,579 --> 00:12:21,919
Deepin Oksu is a modern fresh pasta restaurant.

266
00:12:22,219 --> 00:12:25,418
The third is an Asian restaurant at Euljiro 3-ga.

267
00:12:25,419 --> 00:12:28,089
A restaurant that opened recently called Deepin Noir.

268
00:12:28,489 --> 00:12:30,359
I own these four restaurants.

269
00:12:31,159 --> 00:12:34,799
Many people think that Deepin is owned by Chef Yun Nam No.

270
00:12:34,959 --> 00:12:37,228
I am Nam No's boss.

271
00:12:37,229 --> 00:12:39,099
(Lee Seung Jae, the head chef at Deepin)

272
00:12:39,569 --> 00:12:40,599
The sauce.

273
00:12:41,499 --> 00:12:42,539
Sauce.

274
00:12:44,669 --> 00:12:45,909
What are you selling today?

275
00:12:46,369 --> 00:12:49,179
We're selling XO sauce pasta.

276
00:12:50,239 --> 00:12:54,219
Today, we prepared XO shrimp fresh pasta.

277
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:57,919
(XO shrimp fresh pasta, 14.9 dollars)

278
00:12:58,349 --> 00:13:00,689
For the pasta, we'll bring the dough...

279
00:13:01,559 --> 00:13:04,029
and use a pasta machine on-site...

280
00:13:04,189 --> 00:13:06,459
to make fresh pasta.

281
00:13:07,729 --> 00:13:10,129
Since we're called The Sauce,

282
00:13:10,469 --> 00:13:12,129
we'll make all our sauces from scratch.

283
00:13:12,869 --> 00:13:15,569
To increase the aroma of shrimp shells,

284
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,039
we extract shrimp oil...

285
00:13:17,209 --> 00:13:19,839
and add rayu which is slightly spicy.

286
00:13:19,939 --> 00:13:23,439
(Vegetable stock)

287
00:13:24,049 --> 00:13:26,779
For the XO sauce, we combine dried seafood,

288
00:13:27,479 --> 00:13:30,419
chilli powder, and rayu...

289
00:13:31,049 --> 00:13:34,589
to create a spicy and savoury sauce.

290
00:13:36,659 --> 00:13:39,659
(XO sauce)

291
00:13:40,259 --> 00:13:42,159
(When the order comes in)

292
00:13:42,529 --> 00:13:44,829
Can you set up each sauce?

293
00:13:46,099 --> 00:13:48,438
(With chewy fresh pasta)

294
00:13:48,439 --> 00:13:50,369
We need to stir it, or it will get stuck.

295
00:13:55,079 --> 00:13:56,808
Shrimp and scallion.

296
00:13:56,809 --> 00:13:58,149
(It will be finished with shrimp and scallion.)

297
00:14:01,949 --> 00:14:03,379
Seung Jae, are we done after making ice cream?

298
00:14:03,579 --> 00:14:05,619
Let's make ice cream somehow.

299
00:14:06,219 --> 00:14:08,789
We didn't think anyone would make desserts.

300
00:14:08,919 --> 00:14:10,559
To target the gap in the market,

301
00:14:10,689 --> 00:14:12,489
we wanted to sell freshly made ice cream.

302
00:14:13,259 --> 00:14:14,429
Seung Jae, there's no dessert.

303
00:14:15,159 --> 00:14:18,098
People could eat somewhere else, but have ice cream at our place.

304
00:14:18,099 --> 00:14:20,969
Actually, we came here a week ago to scout the area.

305
00:14:21,099 --> 00:14:22,269
Seung Jae, where are we now?

306
00:14:22,869 --> 00:14:26,069
We're here in Sejong to do some research in advance.

307
00:14:27,209 --> 00:14:28,239
We're in Sejong.

308
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:31,409
The sun is very strong.

309
00:14:33,549 --> 00:14:35,148
When it's sunny, it gets very hot.

310
00:14:35,149 --> 00:14:37,418
When the sun goes down, it gets cold.

311
00:14:37,419 --> 00:14:38,889
There's a big temperature difference between day and night.

312
00:14:39,149 --> 00:14:42,319
It'd be good to provide a cold dessert during lunch.

313
00:14:43,759 --> 00:14:45,758
Seung Jae, keep your eye on it so that it doesn't overflow.

314
00:14:45,759 --> 00:14:47,859
- This is the most important.
- You know that, right?

315
00:14:47,959 --> 00:14:49,459
It's over once it overflows.

316
00:14:53,529 --> 00:14:55,199
Our olive ice cream is...

317
00:14:55,439 --> 00:14:58,709
based on milk, cream, and sugar.

318
00:14:59,309 --> 00:15:00,979
It's boiled at a temperature between 80°C and 85°C.

319
00:15:02,139 --> 00:15:05,548
We mix them over a double boiler so the egg yolks get cooked...

320
00:15:05,549 --> 00:15:06,749
and pasteurized.

321
00:15:08,749 --> 00:15:09,819
All right.

322
00:15:10,519 --> 00:15:12,849
After decreasing the temperature of the ice cream base,

323
00:15:13,149 --> 00:15:15,889
we add extra virgin olive oil.

324
00:15:15,989 --> 00:15:18,258
We gradually add the ingredients while whisking...

325
00:15:18,259 --> 00:15:19,529
to emulsify the mixture.

326
00:15:20,489 --> 00:15:22,899
Once the emulsion is stable, the mixture thickens.

327
00:15:23,299 --> 00:15:25,469
(Ice cream maker)

328
00:15:26,599 --> 00:15:28,498
When the thickened mixture gets frozen,

329
00:15:28,499 --> 00:15:30,269
it turns into dense ice cream.

330
00:15:32,839 --> 00:15:34,908
I think it takes exactly an hour.

331
00:15:34,909 --> 00:15:37,079
(The ice cream base is ready.)

332
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:39,378
With cold ice cream,

333
00:15:39,379 --> 00:15:41,649
let's try to win during the lunch service.

334
00:15:44,149 --> 00:15:48,319
Round 1 of 1,000 dollar sales race starts now.

335
00:15:48,519 --> 00:15:49,989
The customers are here.

336
00:15:50,519 --> 00:15:51,529
Seung Jae, they're here.

337
00:15:51,759 --> 00:15:52,888
Shall we order pasta?

338
00:15:52,889 --> 00:15:54,458
- This looks good.
- Where?

339
00:15:54,459 --> 00:15:55,659
Fresh pasta.

340
00:15:56,959 --> 00:15:58,469
Pasta is irresistible.

341
00:15:59,299 --> 00:16:01,439
You realise that we already ordered a lot, right?

342
00:16:01,569 --> 00:16:03,069
My chicken is for 2 to 3 people.

343
00:16:04,209 --> 00:16:05,739
- How much was it?
- It was 28 dollars.

344
00:16:05,869 --> 00:16:07,739
- That's why it's expensive.
- It's not bad, right?

345
00:16:08,539 --> 00:16:09,738
Do you want some fresh pasta?

346
00:16:09,739 --> 00:16:11,308
- All right.
- Let's take a look around first.

347
00:16:11,309 --> 00:16:12,409
Okay.

348
00:16:12,979 --> 00:16:14,579
They're passing us by.

349
00:16:15,179 --> 00:16:16,549
Please help us.

350
00:16:17,249 --> 00:16:20,419
I also crave some fresh pasta.

351
00:16:20,889 --> 00:16:22,489
If it looks good, come and eat.

352
00:16:23,559 --> 00:16:25,089
Please come and eat.

353
00:16:27,059 --> 00:16:29,098
- It looks good.
- Let's get ice cream for dessert.

354
00:16:29,099 --> 00:16:30,529
After taking a look around...

355
00:16:32,569 --> 00:16:34,439
None of them are getting our fresh pasta.

356
00:16:35,539 --> 00:16:37,608
If just one person would taste it,

357
00:16:37,609 --> 00:16:38,969
- it would be better for the sales.
- Exactly.

358
00:16:40,409 --> 00:16:41,439
Pasta.

359
00:16:42,309 --> 00:16:43,809
I'd like one pasta.

360
00:16:45,579 --> 00:16:47,849
- Shrimp fresh pasta?
- Yes, pasta.

361
00:16:48,579 --> 00:16:51,348
They're coming.

362
00:16:51,349 --> 00:16:52,449
Yes.

363
00:16:53,589 --> 00:16:55,018
It feels like when I got my first order...

364
00:16:55,019 --> 00:16:56,189
- after opening my restaurant.
- Exactly.

365
00:16:59,029 --> 00:17:00,059
Why doesn't it work?

366
00:17:00,159 --> 00:17:02,059
Why? Does it not work?

367
00:17:02,859 --> 00:17:03,929
What's wrong?

368
00:17:07,399 --> 00:17:08,739
Didn't they pay?

369
00:17:10,809 --> 00:17:13,269
They can't do it. Something's not working.

370
00:17:13,939 --> 00:17:17,239
(A sudden internet connection issue)

371
00:17:19,479 --> 00:17:20,579
They can't do it.

372
00:17:20,679 --> 00:17:21,778
(Sighing)

373
00:17:21,779 --> 00:17:22,819
This is driving me crazy.

374
00:17:23,479 --> 00:17:26,289
(Due to the blind sales rule, the chefs cannot go outside.)

375
00:17:26,489 --> 00:17:27,819
The internet got disconnected.

376
00:17:28,159 --> 00:17:31,329
(Contrary to their anxiousness, customers gather one after another.)

377
00:17:31,559 --> 00:17:32,559
- Do it again?
- Yes.

378
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:34,799
There's an issue with the internet connection.

379
00:17:35,199 --> 00:17:36,929
The tablet isn't working.

380
00:17:38,469 --> 00:17:41,999
(Meanwhile, the next door gets one order after another.)

381
00:17:42,869 --> 00:17:44,339
How come you're getting so many orders?

382
00:17:44,839 --> 00:17:46,369
I don't know. I can't focus. Don't talk to me.

383
00:17:46,669 --> 00:17:48,479
Don't talk to me. This is driving me crazy.

384
00:17:50,709 --> 00:17:52,309
I felt very irritated.

385
00:17:52,749 --> 00:17:54,179
"We're not selling any?"

386
00:17:56,249 --> 00:17:57,689
It hurt my pride a lot.

387
00:17:59,549 --> 00:18:02,659
I got anxious thinking that I could actually finish last.

388
00:18:03,089 --> 00:18:04,959
Why isn't it working? Why aren't we getting the order sheets?

389
00:18:06,889 --> 00:18:11,469
(The time goes by.)

390
00:18:11,929 --> 00:18:12,968
I'm worried.

391
00:18:12,969 --> 00:18:13,969
(Current time: 11:29am)

392
00:18:14,269 --> 00:18:16,839
It's been more than ten minutes since our tablet stopped working.

393
00:18:19,409 --> 00:18:22,439
I felt very impatient.

394
00:18:22,879 --> 00:18:24,048
They might leave the queue...

395
00:18:24,049 --> 00:18:26,249
because there are 20 options they can choose from.

396
00:18:26,379 --> 00:18:28,279
There's no reason to wait in a queue.

397
00:18:28,879 --> 00:18:30,478
(Glancing)

398
00:18:30,479 --> 00:18:31,519
But...

399
00:18:32,149 --> 00:18:34,359
This is lunchtime. Time is money.

400
00:18:34,589 --> 00:18:36,188
- Shall we go somewhere else?
- Shall we?

401
00:18:36,189 --> 00:18:37,488
Yes.

402
00:18:37,489 --> 00:18:38,889
- This won't do.
- Okay.

403
00:18:39,989 --> 00:18:43,629
(In the end, some customers leave the queue.)

404
00:18:44,429 --> 00:18:47,669
(Sang Hyun was observing the situation.)

405
00:18:48,539 --> 00:18:50,239
Seung Jae, get ready.

406
00:18:50,809 --> 00:18:52,039
I got it.

407
00:18:53,269 --> 00:18:55,479
Shrimps. Cook the shrimps first.

408
00:18:56,179 --> 00:18:58,009
I'll undercook three portions.

409
00:18:58,449 --> 00:18:59,949
Let's believe the orders will come through.

410
00:19:07,149 --> 00:19:09,118
When you do business and provide services,

411
00:19:09,119 --> 00:19:10,489
you come across so many variables.

412
00:19:12,289 --> 00:19:13,988
I started cooking with the thought...

413
00:19:13,989 --> 00:19:15,559
that I wouldn't finish last or second last.

414
00:19:18,329 --> 00:19:20,068
The first street restaurant...

415
00:19:20,069 --> 00:19:23,199
to achieve the sales of 500 dollars...

416
00:19:23,739 --> 00:19:25,509
- is The Star In My Heart.
- What?

417
00:19:26,169 --> 00:19:27,579
- Five hundred dollars already?
- The Star In My Heart...

418
00:19:27,839 --> 00:19:29,438
achieved 500 dollars.

419
00:19:29,439 --> 00:19:32,379
(Choi Sang Hyun, 0 dollars)

420
00:19:33,009 --> 00:19:35,248
(A bit later)

421
00:19:35,249 --> 00:19:37,078
We have the first street restaurant...

422
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:39,748
to survive the 1,000 dollars sales race.

423
00:19:39,749 --> 00:19:40,759
That's bad news.

424
00:19:41,759 --> 00:19:42,789
Which restaurant is it?

425
00:19:43,759 --> 00:19:47,758
(The Star In My Heart)

426
00:19:47,759 --> 00:19:49,529
We have the first street restaurant...

427
00:19:49,859 --> 00:19:52,598
to survive the 1,000 dollars sales race.

428
00:19:52,599 --> 00:19:53,629
Which is it?

429
00:19:53,999 --> 00:19:55,969
The first restaurant to survive the race...

430
00:19:56,539 --> 00:19:58,038
is The Star In My Heart.

431
00:19:58,039 --> 00:20:00,069
What? We just need to finish this!

432
00:20:00,339 --> 00:20:03,908
(The Star In My Heart, 1,136.83 dollars)

433
00:20:03,909 --> 00:20:04,909
(1st place)

434
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:06,248
- Let's hurry up.
- Quickly.

435
00:20:06,249 --> 00:20:08,679
Let's finish this quickly.

436
00:20:09,019 --> 00:20:10,118
Kimchi cheese.

437
00:20:10,119 --> 00:20:11,588
- Kimchi cheese, hurry up.
- It should be done quickly.

438
00:20:11,589 --> 00:20:12,689
Kimchi cheese.

439
00:20:13,119 --> 00:20:15,588
We should give them a lot more as complimentary.

440
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:17,419
- Let's give them a lot.
- Let's do that.

441
00:20:17,829 --> 00:20:19,859
- This is crazy.
- This is crazy. We survived.

442
00:20:20,089 --> 00:20:21,899
We survived. That's what matters, Jae Beom.

443
00:20:23,029 --> 00:20:24,868
(Arirang House)

444
00:20:24,869 --> 00:20:27,469
(Current sales: 180.78 dollars)

445
00:20:27,669 --> 00:20:29,299
People are still lined up in front of The Star In My Heart.

446
00:20:29,669 --> 00:20:30,869
- Outside?
- Yes.

447
00:20:31,869 --> 00:20:33,468
- It's so crowded.
- What?

448
00:20:33,469 --> 00:20:34,639
It's so crowded.

449
00:20:36,809 --> 00:20:39,549
(Crowded)

450
00:20:40,049 --> 00:20:41,748
There are so many people...

451
00:20:41,749 --> 00:20:43,079
in front of The Star In My Heart.

452
00:20:44,079 --> 00:20:45,719
I hope we get ten more orders.

453
00:20:46,749 --> 00:20:47,759
Please.

454
00:20:48,119 --> 00:20:50,288
Is kimchi cheese chicken ready?

455
00:20:50,289 --> 00:20:51,929
Kimchi cheese...

456
00:20:52,129 --> 00:20:54,089
- with cucumber salad, right?
- Yes.

457
00:20:54,499 --> 00:20:56,129
- Coming now.
- Okay.

458
00:20:58,869 --> 00:21:01,969
(The Star In My Heart is packed with customers.)

459
00:21:02,699 --> 00:21:04,738
Did you come to pick up your food or...

460
00:21:04,739 --> 00:21:05,939
- To pick up.
- Is that so?

461
00:21:06,239 --> 00:21:08,178
- Did you get the message?
- No, so I came to ask.

462
00:21:08,179 --> 00:21:09,208
Right?

463
00:21:09,209 --> 00:21:10,948
- It takes more than 30 minutes.
- You do get it if you keep waiting.

464
00:21:10,949 --> 00:21:11,949
Really?

465
00:21:11,950 --> 00:21:14,108
- When did you order your food?
- About 30 minutes ago.

466
00:21:14,109 --> 00:21:15,379
It's been more than 30 minutes.

467
00:21:15,819 --> 00:21:17,688
- What time did you order?
- At 11:34am.

468
00:21:17,689 --> 00:21:19,388
- I ordered at 11:34am too.
- I ordered at 11:35am.

469
00:21:19,389 --> 00:21:20,389
At 11:35am.

470
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:22,058
I ordered at 11:29am.

471
00:21:22,059 --> 00:21:23,288
And even yours isn't ready yet.

472
00:21:23,289 --> 00:21:26,489
(Current time)

473
00:21:26,689 --> 00:21:28,228
- It's behind you.
- Okay, behind me.

474
00:21:28,229 --> 00:21:32,069
(Their survival is confirmed once they serve all the food.)

475
00:21:32,869 --> 00:21:34,569
Kimchi cheese, 1, 2.

476
00:21:35,769 --> 00:21:37,439
Three, four,

477
00:21:38,939 --> 00:21:40,979
five... Why doesn't it end?

478
00:21:45,779 --> 00:21:47,008
The orders are running behind.

479
00:21:47,009 --> 00:21:48,648
There's one ordered 27 minutes ago.

480
00:21:48,649 --> 00:21:50,219
Really? I'll try to be quick.

481
00:21:50,519 --> 00:21:52,018
We need to serve two kimchi cheese quickly.

482
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:53,319
It's been 30 minutes.

483
00:21:54,359 --> 00:21:55,488
(She quickly serves kimchi cheese, which was running behind.)

484
00:21:55,489 --> 00:21:57,289
It's kimchi cheese. Enjoy.

485
00:21:58,929 --> 00:22:01,558
Kimchi cheese... The called numbers are served.

486
00:22:01,559 --> 00:22:03,429
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

487
00:22:04,399 --> 00:22:05,829
Are you preparing kimchi cheese now?

488
00:22:06,269 --> 00:22:08,569
I made the payment, but I didn't get the number.

489
00:22:08,769 --> 00:22:11,038
It's been a while since I've ordered Korean calcot,

490
00:22:11,039 --> 00:22:12,769
so I'm wondering if the order went through.

491
00:22:13,109 --> 00:22:14,608
- It came through. I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

492
00:22:14,609 --> 00:22:16,579
The orders are running behind.

493
00:22:17,109 --> 00:22:18,608
Jae Beom, Korean calcot needs to be served quickly too.

494
00:22:18,609 --> 00:22:19,779
Okay, Korean calcot.

495
00:22:20,579 --> 00:22:22,019
Do I take out one serving of Korean calcot?

496
00:22:22,379 --> 00:22:23,979
Take out as much as you can.

497
00:22:24,389 --> 00:22:25,889
My hands are suddenly trembling.

498
00:22:26,049 --> 00:22:27,149
Oh, no.

499
00:22:32,029 --> 00:22:33,929
Two Korean calcots.

500
00:22:34,299 --> 00:22:35,299
Thanks.

501
00:22:35,499 --> 00:22:36,699
Oh, dear.

502
00:22:38,099 --> 00:22:40,069
What should I do? I'm having a mental breakdown.

503
00:22:40,629 --> 00:22:43,069
We have a lot of orders piled up.

504
00:22:43,969 --> 00:22:46,439
How many orders do we have left?

505
00:22:47,779 --> 00:22:48,979
Almost...

506
00:22:50,279 --> 00:22:51,809
- thirty-seven.
- What?

507
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,509
We should cancel the order, right?

508
00:22:54,009 --> 00:22:57,519
(The amount of orders piled up is beyond what they can handle.)

509
00:22:57,849 --> 00:23:00,589
- Yes, this...
- We need to cancel the order.

510
00:23:01,489 --> 00:23:03,219
The waiting customers...

511
00:23:03,589 --> 00:23:06,829
Most of them are public officials, come to think of it.

512
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:10,699
I shouldn't waste their precious lunchtime.

513
00:23:10,959 --> 00:23:12,569
I should just cancel their orders.

514
00:23:13,299 --> 00:23:15,038
Can you cancel Korean calcot orders...

515
00:23:15,039 --> 00:23:17,269
from Number 6063 onward?

516
00:23:17,909 --> 00:23:20,469
Hello. Is Number 6063 here?

517
00:23:20,639 --> 00:23:22,478
- Is Number 6063 here?
- Yes?

518
00:23:22,479 --> 00:23:24,678
- It's me.
- Starting from Number 6063,

519
00:23:24,679 --> 00:23:26,779
your orders will be cancelled and refunded.

520
00:23:27,149 --> 00:23:28,519
- Starting with me?
- Yes.

521
00:23:29,579 --> 00:23:30,649
I'm sorry.

522
00:23:31,019 --> 00:23:32,819
But you've waited for a long time.

523
00:23:32,949 --> 00:23:36,018
I'll give you a free bowl of Korean chicken soup each.

524
00:23:36,019 --> 00:23:37,119
It won't take long.

525
00:23:37,319 --> 00:23:39,028
Could you wait for five minutes?

526
00:23:39,029 --> 00:23:40,059
Okay.

527
00:23:40,559 --> 00:23:41,758
Is it sold out?

528
00:23:41,759 --> 00:23:43,828
(Murmuring)

529
00:23:43,829 --> 00:23:46,299
(Korean calcot refunded, 28 dollars deducted)

530
00:23:47,529 --> 00:23:48,798
What time did you make the payment?

531
00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:49,938
I got cut off.

532
00:23:49,939 --> 00:23:51,109
(Total sales excluding the cost: 1,108.83 dollars)

533
00:23:54,539 --> 00:23:55,739
Number 1807.

534
00:23:55,839 --> 00:23:58,309
The first refund has occurred.

535
00:24:00,149 --> 00:24:02,019
- It's on the way.
- The first refund has occurred...

536
00:24:02,249 --> 00:24:04,449
to The Star In My Heart.

537
00:24:05,449 --> 00:24:06,689
- Oh, my gosh.
- A refund?

538
00:24:07,119 --> 00:24:08,589
There's a refund too?

539
00:24:09,589 --> 00:24:10,789
Why a refund?

540
00:24:11,489 --> 00:24:13,289
Yes, a refund can happen.

541
00:24:13,629 --> 00:24:15,228
In what situation do you give them a refund?

542
00:24:15,229 --> 00:24:16,559
Was there something in the food?

543
00:24:17,699 --> 00:24:18,929
Why is that shop so crowded?

544
00:24:19,669 --> 00:24:20,669
What?

545
00:24:20,670 --> 00:24:22,499
- They're murmuring.
- It is tasty, though.

546
00:24:22,669 --> 00:24:24,069
Because the food isn't served.

547
00:24:24,739 --> 00:24:26,109
They take super long to serve the food.

548
00:24:27,569 --> 00:24:29,838
Can you cancel my order too?

549
00:24:29,839 --> 00:24:31,108
What's your number?

550
00:24:31,109 --> 00:24:33,349
- Number 5951.
- Number 5951.

551
00:24:33,949 --> 00:24:35,748
Are you in charge of cancelling the order?

552
00:24:35,749 --> 00:24:38,648
I'll call the person in charge.

553
00:24:38,649 --> 00:24:39,649
Please give us a moment.

554
00:24:39,949 --> 00:24:45,189
(28 dollars deducted)

555
00:24:45,589 --> 00:24:46,759
Six.

556
00:24:46,929 --> 00:24:48,258
- Six.
- Six.

557
00:24:48,259 --> 00:24:49,299
Okay.

558
00:24:50,199 --> 00:24:52,428
All the bills coming in now are the cancellations, right?

559
00:24:52,429 --> 00:24:53,468
Yes.

560
00:24:53,469 --> 00:24:55,439
(Sales: 1,080.83 dollars)

561
00:24:55,899 --> 00:24:57,699
(Sales: 1,052.83 dollars)

562
00:24:58,639 --> 00:24:59,739
I'm scared.

563
00:25:00,569 --> 00:25:01,679
The sound of the bills.

564
00:25:01,909 --> 00:25:05,009
(The Star In My Heart's current sales: 996.83 dollars)

565
00:25:05,479 --> 00:25:07,649
Number 3783, please take your dish.

566
00:25:08,319 --> 00:25:11,819
Next is Number 3949.

567
00:25:15,159 --> 00:25:17,619
The fifth refund has occurred.

568
00:25:18,529 --> 00:25:19,828
- How much are our sales now?
- With this,

569
00:25:19,829 --> 00:25:22,929
the survival of The Star In My Heart has been revoked.

570
00:25:23,259 --> 00:25:24,329
What?

571
00:25:27,229 --> 00:25:32,709
(The Star In My Heart's survival has been revoked.)

572
00:25:33,439 --> 00:25:34,439
What?

573
00:25:35,079 --> 00:25:37,039
They're so strict.

574
00:25:37,509 --> 00:25:40,149
When you give them a refund, the amount is deducted.

575
00:25:41,109 --> 00:25:43,019
"We're not in the safe zone."

576
00:25:43,319 --> 00:25:45,049
That thought suddenly occurred to me.

577
00:25:45,589 --> 00:25:46,689
Cold sweat...

578
00:25:47,149 --> 00:25:50,659
I started to sweat from the top of my head.

579
00:25:51,959 --> 00:25:54,759
How does this make sense?

580
00:25:54,859 --> 00:25:57,998
The survival of The Star In My Heart has been revoked.

581
00:25:57,999 --> 00:25:58,999
What?

582
00:26:05,839 --> 00:26:07,439
- It has been revoked.
- Goodness.

583
00:26:11,079 --> 00:26:12,179
Gosh, what happened?

584
00:26:12,949 --> 00:26:14,149
How can this happen?

585
00:26:15,919 --> 00:26:18,389
They must've gotten another refund.

586
00:26:19,089 --> 00:26:20,919
- It can be revoked?
- It was revoked? What happened?

587
00:26:22,559 --> 00:26:24,629
I'll give you two bowls of Korean chicken soup.

588
00:26:24,829 --> 00:26:26,328
- It's okay.
- Please wait a minute.

589
00:26:26,329 --> 00:26:27,389
It's okay.

590
00:26:28,259 --> 00:26:29,629
It'll be really quick.

591
00:26:30,829 --> 00:26:32,898
(Sighing)

592
00:26:32,899 --> 00:26:34,539
Anyway, we need to serve four.

593
00:26:35,139 --> 00:26:36,738
We need four kimchi chicken.

594
00:26:36,739 --> 00:26:38,339
Okay, four kimchi chicken.

595
00:26:39,309 --> 00:26:41,038
(Even when their survival has been revoked,)

596
00:26:41,039 --> 00:26:43,279
(the business goes on.)

597
00:26:43,409 --> 00:26:44,509
Thank you.

598
00:26:45,279 --> 00:26:47,178
I'm so sorry for taking so long.

599
00:26:47,179 --> 00:26:50,078
I added some lettuce inside so you can make a wrap with it...

600
00:26:50,079 --> 00:26:51,488
along with seasoned bean sprouts.

601
00:26:51,489 --> 00:26:52,918
I'll give you one more potato salad too.

602
00:26:52,919 --> 00:26:54,118
- Thank you.
- I'm so sorry.

603
00:26:54,119 --> 00:26:55,489
- Sorry.
- I'm so sorry.

604
00:26:56,059 --> 00:26:58,559
Hello, here's kimchi cheese.

605
00:26:58,959 --> 00:27:00,028
Thanks for the long wait.

606
00:27:00,029 --> 00:27:01,859
- Thank you.
- I said I'd give you extra, right?

607
00:27:01,999 --> 00:27:04,629
- Yes, thank you. Enjoy the food.
- Enjoy the food.

608
00:27:09,499 --> 00:27:12,508
Honestly speaking, we didn't expect it to be so well-liked.

609
00:27:12,509 --> 00:27:16,338
We had an estimate of the time we'll take to make 1,000 dollars.

610
00:27:16,339 --> 00:27:17,948
But we had way more customers,

611
00:27:17,949 --> 00:27:19,509
and it took a lot faster than we thought.

612
00:27:21,349 --> 00:27:22,349
This is insane.

613
00:27:22,350 --> 00:27:23,419
Amazing.

614
00:27:23,519 --> 00:27:24,648
Hold on.

615
00:27:24,649 --> 00:27:26,988
(And...)

616
00:27:26,989 --> 00:27:29,418
Chicken gets dry...

617
00:27:29,419 --> 00:27:31,428
if you cook it beforehand,

618
00:27:31,429 --> 00:27:33,889
so we decided to cook it as we sell.

619
00:27:34,059 --> 00:27:37,659
(They didn't cook the chicken beforehand.)

620
00:27:38,199 --> 00:27:41,029
Can you melt one cheese in the microwave?

621
00:27:41,539 --> 00:27:42,739
The cheese is giving us trouble.

622
00:27:44,299 --> 00:27:47,308
In every business, greed leads to trouble.

623
00:27:47,309 --> 00:27:50,238
(They've prepared too many menus.)

624
00:27:50,239 --> 00:27:52,648
We didn't think about the efficiency of the flow,

625
00:27:52,649 --> 00:27:55,249
and we didn't expect the customers to rush in at once.

626
00:27:55,549 --> 00:27:57,279
That was a mistake on my part.

627
00:27:59,019 --> 00:28:01,219
The refunded amount is 310 dollars.

628
00:28:02,819 --> 00:28:03,988
(Refund amount: 311 dollars)

629
00:28:03,989 --> 00:28:05,388
(Refund amount: 311 dollars, Total sales: 1,136.83 dollars)

630
00:28:05,389 --> 00:28:07,259
(Refund amount: 311 dollars, Total sales: 825.83 dollars)

631
00:28:07,829 --> 00:28:09,899
The current number of survived restaurants...

632
00:28:10,859 --> 00:28:11,999
is zero.

633
00:28:13,769 --> 00:28:15,799
They're really playing with my nerves.

634
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:18,239
They could lose the lead.

635
00:28:19,169 --> 00:28:20,869
Nothing's fixed yet. We still have the chance.

636
00:28:21,479 --> 00:28:22,609
We can win first place.

637
00:28:23,239 --> 00:28:25,208
Can we win first place, Ji Beom?

638
00:28:25,209 --> 00:28:26,209
We can.

639
00:28:26,210 --> 00:28:27,849
- Have you not given up?
- I've not given up.

640
00:28:28,149 --> 00:28:29,218
You can do it, right?

641
00:28:29,219 --> 00:28:30,448
I can. You can do it, right?

642
00:28:30,449 --> 00:28:31,649
- Of course.
- Okay.

643
00:28:31,789 --> 00:28:33,349
It isn't over until it's over.

644
00:28:35,159 --> 00:28:38,128
(Which restaurant will become the new winner...)

645
00:28:38,129 --> 00:28:40,289
(of the 1,000 dollar sales race?)

646
00:28:43,559 --> 00:28:44,669
I'm sorry.

647
00:28:45,029 --> 00:28:46,929
Here's our complimentary dish.

648
00:28:47,299 --> 00:28:49,199
They're next to us, so I can see what's going on.

649
00:28:51,169 --> 00:28:52,639
Something must've happened.

650
00:28:54,509 --> 00:28:56,409
They had to make refunds because their food sold out, right?

651
00:28:56,679 --> 00:28:57,779
Sorry?

652
00:28:58,149 --> 00:28:59,779
- They ran out of the ingredients?
- I think so.

653
00:29:00,879 --> 00:29:02,779
(There's a minor misunderstanding.)

654
00:29:02,949 --> 00:29:04,689
We said we'd win by a landslide.

655
00:29:06,689 --> 00:29:09,489
Instead, we were overpowered by the stall next door.

656
00:29:10,819 --> 00:29:12,589
It's okay.

657
00:29:12,929 --> 00:29:14,189
We'll go at our pace.

658
00:29:15,429 --> 00:29:16,528
Things aren't bad now.

659
00:29:16,529 --> 00:29:17,929
Right, we'll go at our pace.

660
00:29:19,429 --> 00:29:20,828
Koony? Hoony?

661
00:29:20,829 --> 00:29:22,269
- There's a shop called Hoony?
- Koony.

662
00:29:22,539 --> 00:29:24,569
I've been in this business for a long time,

663
00:29:24,839 --> 00:29:26,669
which means I know almost everyone.

664
00:29:26,839 --> 00:29:29,209
But I've never seen him before, which got me curious.

665
00:29:29,439 --> 00:29:30,579
He's in very good shape.

666
00:29:31,409 --> 00:29:34,649
He doesn't look like he's a chef.

667
00:29:35,149 --> 00:29:36,649
Exactly. He looks so ripped.

668
00:29:49,559 --> 00:29:53,229
Hello. I'm Lee Sung Hoon.

669
00:29:54,699 --> 00:29:57,169
I run Just Tendong in Yeonnam-dong,

670
00:29:58,669 --> 00:29:59,909
Dining Yagyeong,

671
00:30:00,339 --> 00:30:01,709
and Yeonnam Kalguksu.

672
00:30:02,239 --> 00:30:05,179
I've launched 15 brands so far,

673
00:30:05,349 --> 00:30:07,579
which a lot of customers paid their visits to.

674
00:30:08,549 --> 00:30:11,419
(Lee Sung Hoon, Yeonnam-dong Legend)

675
00:30:12,349 --> 00:30:13,589
Should I remove the apron?

676
00:30:13,889 --> 00:30:15,418
- Sorry?
- Should I remove the apron?

677
00:30:15,419 --> 00:30:17,159
- Apron? Why?
- Yes.

678
00:30:17,489 --> 00:30:18,929
It looks a bit strange.

679
00:30:20,459 --> 00:30:22,799
We must wear it to look like chefs.

680
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:27,329
Don't you remember how they reacted?

681
00:30:29,339 --> 00:30:31,608
They didn't cheer for us...

682
00:30:31,609 --> 00:30:32,809
or anything.

683
00:30:33,769 --> 00:30:36,309
Actually, when the name "Koony" is announced,

684
00:30:36,879 --> 00:30:39,179
the crowd goes silent.

685
00:30:40,249 --> 00:30:41,649
Nobody knows us.

686
00:30:41,949 --> 00:30:43,948
- BokBok, Lee Yeon Bok.
- Chef Lee Yeon Bok.

687
00:30:43,949 --> 00:30:45,349
It's Chef Lee Yeon Bok.

688
00:30:46,919 --> 00:30:48,089
Go Seok Hyun.

689
00:30:51,489 --> 00:30:53,329
Everything About Tteokbokki.

690
00:30:54,189 --> 00:30:55,429
He's going all out.

691
00:30:56,129 --> 00:30:58,399
Koony, Lee Sung Hoon.

692
00:30:59,929 --> 00:31:03,099
Special black ramen, 13 dollars.

693
00:31:07,969 --> 00:31:10,078
- No reaction for ours.
- I know, right.

694
00:31:10,079 --> 00:31:11,548
When I first showed up,

695
00:31:11,549 --> 00:31:13,308
they were like, "Who is he?"

696
00:31:13,309 --> 00:31:15,349
I felt that in their eyes.

697
00:31:15,979 --> 00:31:18,919
(During the opening ceremony)

698
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:20,349
"Yeonnam-dong Legend?"

699
00:31:21,449 --> 00:31:24,259
"Yeonnam-dong Legend?" That's my area.

700
00:31:25,229 --> 00:31:26,858
We never appeared...

701
00:31:26,859 --> 00:31:28,898
on TV shows...

702
00:31:28,899 --> 00:31:30,228
nor are we famous.

703
00:31:30,229 --> 00:31:31,329
Who is he?

704
00:31:32,199 --> 00:31:33,199
Who is he?

705
00:31:33,329 --> 00:31:35,239
- Who is he?
- I don't know.

706
00:31:37,939 --> 00:31:38,969
Hello.

707
00:31:39,139 --> 00:31:40,208
Hello.

708
00:31:40,209 --> 00:31:41,209
(Lee Sung Hoon, "Who is he?" Just Tendong, Dining Yagyeong,)

709
00:31:41,209 --> 00:31:42,209
(Yeonnam Kalguksu, launched 15 brands in total)

710
00:31:43,639 --> 00:31:45,649
So when ours was announced, they didn't murmur.

711
00:31:46,709 --> 00:31:47,779
They went silent.

712
00:31:52,749 --> 00:31:54,289
Who gave us...

713
00:31:55,359 --> 00:31:57,618
Who gave us an empty bottle of sake...

714
00:31:57,619 --> 00:31:59,029
- Did you use it?
- I used it.

715
00:32:03,029 --> 00:32:04,868
I thought, "We may be underdogs,"

716
00:32:04,869 --> 00:32:06,399
"but how could they treat us this poorly?"

717
00:32:07,629 --> 00:32:10,399
All the other chefs are famous.

718
00:32:10,539 --> 00:32:13,309
So the term "underdog" would describe us well.

719
00:32:13,639 --> 00:32:14,979
Despite that,

720
00:32:15,609 --> 00:32:16,738
I was confident.

721
00:32:16,739 --> 00:32:19,079
And let's not lose in terms of spirits.

722
00:32:19,549 --> 00:32:22,518
We prepared special black ramen.

723
00:32:22,519 --> 00:32:25,689
It's tonkotsu-base ramen,

724
00:32:26,149 --> 00:32:28,219
and we added squid ink to it.

725
00:32:28,319 --> 00:32:31,559
When you stir the noodles, the broth turns black.

726
00:32:31,929 --> 00:32:35,928
The broth takes some time...

727
00:32:35,929 --> 00:32:37,629
to taste deep.

728
00:32:41,869 --> 00:32:44,399
Let's sell 77 bowls of ramen which was prepared for 7 hours.

729
00:32:45,339 --> 00:32:47,338
That's how the slogan became 777.

730
00:32:47,339 --> 00:32:49,808
(777, just for today, to sell 77 bowls, we prepared for 7 hours.)

731
00:32:49,809 --> 00:32:52,178
After searing pork shoulder,

732
00:32:52,179 --> 00:32:54,049
we cooked it for five hours.

733
00:32:55,419 --> 00:32:57,448
Place the ink on the bowl.

734
00:32:57,449 --> 00:33:01,488
(Ink on the bowl)

735
00:33:01,489 --> 00:33:05,028
(Noodles)

736
00:33:05,029 --> 00:33:06,158
Pour the broth.

737
00:33:06,159 --> 00:33:08,698
(Broth)

738
00:33:08,699 --> 00:33:09,758
Two slices of char siu.

739
00:33:09,759 --> 00:33:10,858
(Two slices of char siu)

740
00:33:10,859 --> 00:33:12,099
Two pieces of seasoned boiled eggs.

741
00:33:12,499 --> 00:33:14,169
Two slices of dried laver, a bit of fermented bamboo shoots,

742
00:33:14,299 --> 00:33:17,438
sliced green onion, and some pepper to finish it.

743
00:33:17,439 --> 00:33:18,439
(Finishing it with pepper)

744
00:33:21,109 --> 00:33:23,809
(Special black ramen, 13 dollars)

745
00:33:24,979 --> 00:33:26,549
- This ramen is delicious.
- Yes.

746
00:33:27,409 --> 00:33:29,178
It tastes fine.

747
00:33:29,179 --> 00:33:30,179
It's thick.

748
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:31,578
What's black, though?

749
00:33:31,579 --> 00:33:32,748
- I wonder.
- The noodles, maybe?

750
00:33:32,749 --> 00:33:34,089
- The noodles are white.
- The noodles are white.

751
00:33:35,659 --> 00:33:37,858
- Black...
- I don't know what's black.

752
00:33:37,859 --> 00:33:38,859
I'm curious.

753
00:33:38,989 --> 00:33:40,688
(Stirring)

754
00:33:40,689 --> 00:33:41,959
Oh, black.

755
00:33:42,999 --> 00:33:44,228
I see.

756
00:33:44,229 --> 00:33:45,568
- What is it?
- There's squid ink.

757
00:33:45,569 --> 00:33:47,099
- It suddenly...
- At the bottom of the bowl.

758
00:33:47,169 --> 00:33:49,199
This must be the twist.

759
00:33:51,039 --> 00:33:52,168
The intention was for the soup...

760
00:33:52,169 --> 00:33:54,979
to turn black when you stir the noodles.

761
00:33:55,479 --> 00:33:58,279
I wanted to make dishes which broke the prejudice.

762
00:33:58,409 --> 00:34:00,678
Something black keeps coming up.

763
00:34:00,679 --> 00:34:01,848
You're right. It was all the way...

764
00:34:01,849 --> 00:34:02,979
- at the bottom.
- What's that?

765
00:34:03,019 --> 00:34:05,289
Did they intentionally make it so it'll turn black as you eat?

766
00:34:05,449 --> 00:34:07,289
- Where is it coming from?
- Exactly.

767
00:34:08,049 --> 00:34:09,718
It tastes different after mixing it.

768
00:34:09,719 --> 00:34:10,789
Yes.

769
00:34:11,219 --> 00:34:12,928
The black thing was at the bottom.

770
00:34:12,929 --> 00:34:15,499
- Goodness.
- Why didn't the chef tell me this?

771
00:34:17,299 --> 00:34:18,328
Right.

772
00:34:18,329 --> 00:34:19,398
- I taste squid.
- My gosh.

773
00:34:19,399 --> 00:34:20,899
If they sell it at 13 dollars, I'll go eat it every day.

774
00:34:22,039 --> 00:34:24,069
Tae Hee, we sold 455 dollars.

775
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:25,408
That's a lot.

776
00:34:25,409 --> 00:34:28,009
(Current sales rank: 13th, 455 dollars)

777
00:34:31,809 --> 00:34:36,049
The number of street restaurants which achieved 500 dollars sales...

778
00:34:36,949 --> 00:34:38,519
is eight.

779
00:34:43,219 --> 00:34:44,259
Jo Seo Hyung.

780
00:34:45,629 --> 00:34:46,759
Kim Mi Ryeong.

781
00:34:48,499 --> 00:34:49,629
Kim Hoon.

782
00:34:52,029 --> 00:34:53,069
And...

783
00:34:53,699 --> 00:34:54,829
This is bad.

784
00:34:54,999 --> 00:34:56,099
- Why?
- Jung Ho Young.

785
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:57,338
Why?

786
00:34:57,339 --> 00:34:58,869
Deep-fried shrimps are way too crispy.

787
00:34:59,539 --> 00:35:01,239
They're queuing up in front of Hohyunghojae.

788
00:35:02,239 --> 00:35:04,838
Insert your card or press a button.

789
00:35:04,839 --> 00:35:06,808
(Hohyunghojae)

790
00:35:06,809 --> 00:35:07,949
One futomaki.

791
00:35:08,009 --> 00:35:09,019
Another one?

792
00:35:09,449 --> 00:35:11,849
Say "thank you," not "another one."

793
00:35:12,519 --> 00:35:13,818
Another one came in.

794
00:35:13,819 --> 00:35:15,488
Don't think about the orders. Just roll it up.

795
00:35:15,489 --> 00:35:16,559
Roll it up?

796
00:35:17,189 --> 00:35:18,289
This is crazy.

797
00:35:18,729 --> 00:35:21,759
- Yes, it...
- I think we're the busiest.

798
00:35:22,929 --> 00:35:24,228
I don't think so.

799
00:35:24,229 --> 00:35:25,229
Really?

800
00:35:25,899 --> 00:35:27,198
Hello.

801
00:35:27,199 --> 00:35:30,198
I run an udon restaurant and an izakaya...

802
00:35:30,199 --> 00:35:33,269
in Seoul and Jeju Island. I'm Jung Ho Young.

803
00:35:34,269 --> 00:35:36,578
I think I'm the one...

804
00:35:36,579 --> 00:35:39,448
who popularized Japanese cuisine in Korea...

805
00:35:39,449 --> 00:35:41,109
by running an udon restaurant and an izakaya.

806
00:35:42,479 --> 00:35:44,049
Didn't I tell you to clean the knife?

807
00:35:44,249 --> 00:35:46,348
I did. Did I not?

808
00:35:46,349 --> 00:35:48,119
You must clean it immediately after you use it.

809
00:35:48,989 --> 00:35:49,989
I'm sorry.

810
00:35:52,529 --> 00:35:54,458
(Hohyunghojae's opening crew, Song Hoon)

811
00:35:54,459 --> 00:35:55,559
It won't be easy.

812
00:35:56,029 --> 00:35:57,928
Chef Jung Ho Young and Chef Song Hoon.

813
00:35:57,929 --> 00:35:59,699
I was so shocked.

814
00:36:00,429 --> 00:36:01,869
Isn't it cheating?

815
00:36:03,099 --> 00:36:05,969
I'm close with Chef Song Hoon.

816
00:36:06,139 --> 00:36:09,909
Chef Song Hoon is good at...

817
00:36:10,009 --> 00:36:13,148
both fine dining and casual dishes.

818
00:36:13,149 --> 00:36:14,309
He cooks Korean cuisine well too.

819
00:36:15,649 --> 00:36:18,349
I could use him in various ways.

820
00:36:18,749 --> 00:36:19,949
That's what I thought.

821
00:36:21,149 --> 00:36:23,159
We don't need help.

822
00:36:23,359 --> 00:36:24,919
This restaurant is run by us two brothers...

823
00:36:25,189 --> 00:36:26,329
working together.

824
00:36:27,159 --> 00:36:28,159
Right?

825
00:36:28,529 --> 00:36:31,299
"Ho" from Jung Ho Young, and "hyung" means older brother.

826
00:36:31,629 --> 00:36:32,929
I'm his younger brother.

827
00:36:33,199 --> 00:36:35,199
Who just laughs.

828
00:36:35,939 --> 00:36:38,369
The dish we prepared is...

829
00:36:39,009 --> 00:36:40,769
a futomaki meal.

830
00:36:41,839 --> 00:36:44,639
(Futomaki meal)

831
00:36:44,839 --> 00:36:46,548
The customers are in their 30s and 40s.

832
00:36:46,549 --> 00:36:48,379
The civil servants of Sejong are young.

833
00:36:49,249 --> 00:36:53,019
What kind of food would the civil servants in Sejong like?

834
00:36:53,119 --> 00:36:55,789
The gender ratio is about 52 to 48.

835
00:36:56,189 --> 00:36:58,859
As there are many female customers,

836
00:36:59,129 --> 00:37:01,629
they must expect something pretty and simple to eat.

837
00:37:01,759 --> 00:37:03,699
One option could be gimbap.

838
00:37:07,099 --> 00:37:09,099
Spreading the rice will be tough.

839
00:37:09,299 --> 00:37:11,099
Spreading the rice thinly is challenging.

840
00:37:12,169 --> 00:37:15,239
For futomaki, you stick two sheets of dried laver together,

841
00:37:16,539 --> 00:37:19,879
add a fluffy rolled omelet, pickled radish,

842
00:37:20,879 --> 00:37:21,919
burdock,

843
00:37:24,549 --> 00:37:26,289
and celtuce.

844
00:37:28,919 --> 00:37:30,489
Just look at how much salmon is added.

845
00:37:31,119 --> 00:37:32,829
It has raw salmon in it.

846
00:37:33,929 --> 00:37:35,059
Shrimp.

847
00:37:37,929 --> 00:37:38,969
Deep-fried shrimp.

848
00:37:41,369 --> 00:37:42,999
And sliced cucumbers.

849
00:37:45,039 --> 00:37:46,608
It's rolled thick.

850
00:37:46,609 --> 00:37:50,639
Thick to the point where you need to open your mouth wide to eat it.

851
00:37:58,049 --> 00:37:59,119
It's soft.

852
00:38:02,089 --> 00:38:03,659
- You've got rice.
- Pick it off for me.

853
00:38:06,259 --> 00:38:07,389
Why here of all places?

854
00:38:10,499 --> 00:38:12,399
(Printing)

855
00:38:12,599 --> 00:38:14,269
What? It's here!

856
00:38:14,529 --> 00:38:15,599
- What?
- An order.

857
00:38:15,869 --> 00:38:16,969
Quiet down, will you?

858
00:38:18,399 --> 00:38:19,769
Two... One futomaki.

859
00:38:20,069 --> 00:38:21,609
- One futomaki?
- One futomaki.

860
00:38:21,879 --> 00:38:22,939
One futomaki.

861
00:38:23,109 --> 00:38:25,008
I'll get the soup. It won't take long, right?

862
00:38:25,009 --> 00:38:27,249
No, it won't. Give me a second.

863
00:38:27,809 --> 00:38:28,978
- I'm kind of...
- We are...

864
00:38:28,979 --> 00:38:30,678
professionals, and yet, it's nerve-racking.

865
00:38:30,679 --> 00:38:32,849
Right? I'm getting excited.

866
00:38:32,989 --> 00:38:34,189
- Gosh.
- Oh, dear.

867
00:38:34,449 --> 00:38:35,658
- One futomaki.
- One futomaki. Okay.

868
00:38:35,659 --> 00:38:37,389
It's 15 dollars. No, 14.50 dollars.

869
00:38:38,889 --> 00:38:40,759
Okay. Nice.

870
00:38:42,129 --> 00:38:43,998
Okay. Freshly deep-fried chicken.

871
00:38:43,999 --> 00:38:45,028
I leave it to you.

872
00:38:45,029 --> 00:38:47,899
- Put a bit more in.
- What? Okay.

873
00:38:53,969 --> 00:38:56,079
(Hello.)

874
00:38:56,239 --> 00:38:57,379
The futomaki is done.

875
00:38:58,009 --> 00:39:00,179
It feels like it's ours. It is ours.

876
00:39:00,749 --> 00:39:02,279
Thank you for the meal.

877
00:39:04,019 --> 00:39:05,749
- Oh, my.
- I'm getting our other dish.

878
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:08,319
- How is it?
- It looks really good.

879
00:39:09,919 --> 00:39:10,919
Goodness.

880
00:39:11,389 --> 00:39:12,759
It looks really good.

881
00:39:13,159 --> 00:39:14,929
Nice, it's a hit.

882
00:39:15,959 --> 00:39:17,029
I'm relieved.

883
00:39:17,199 --> 00:39:19,429
Getting off to a strong start is important.

884
00:39:19,769 --> 00:39:21,429
- It was nice.
- Only when it's pretty...

885
00:39:21,769 --> 00:39:22,968
will customers be like, "What's that?"

886
00:39:22,969 --> 00:39:24,199
Word of mouth is needed.

887
00:39:25,039 --> 00:39:27,539
(Spreading by word of mouth)

888
00:39:27,839 --> 00:39:29,038
The futomaki looks hearty.

889
00:39:29,039 --> 00:39:30,739
- Right? I'm getting the futomaki.
- Okay.

890
00:39:31,179 --> 00:39:32,379
There's futomaki.

891
00:39:33,609 --> 00:39:34,909
Futomaki!

892
00:39:35,719 --> 00:39:37,349
- The futomaki looks good.
- Right?

893
00:39:39,619 --> 00:39:42,558
Since the customers are civil servants, word travels fast...

894
00:39:42,559 --> 00:39:45,159
to the customers in the next time slot.

895
00:39:46,529 --> 00:39:48,899
(As a result,)

896
00:39:49,599 --> 00:39:53,869
(there's a line only at Hohyunghojae.)

897
00:39:54,799 --> 00:39:56,699
- This won't fit in one bite.
- Exactly.

898
00:39:57,969 --> 00:39:59,668
Is this real futomaki?

899
00:39:59,669 --> 00:40:02,409
The futomaki I had in the past must all have been fake.

900
00:40:02,739 --> 00:40:04,308
- It's the size of my fist.
- It sure is big.

901
00:40:04,309 --> 00:40:05,549
- It's the size of my fist.
- Amazing.

902
00:40:06,379 --> 00:40:09,379
(Ho Young rolled it by pressing it down endlessly.)

903
00:40:10,719 --> 00:40:13,019
(Jumbo futomaki)

904
00:40:13,849 --> 00:40:15,288
You can't fit it in your mouth.

905
00:40:15,289 --> 00:40:16,319
Oh, my.

906
00:40:20,159 --> 00:40:21,729
I can't talk now.

907
00:40:24,599 --> 00:40:25,869
Shouldn't you eat it horizontally?

908
00:40:26,529 --> 00:40:27,929
It won't work if you eat it vertically.

909
00:40:31,699 --> 00:40:32,709
Is it good?

910
00:40:33,539 --> 00:40:35,169
He can't talk right now.

911
00:40:35,339 --> 00:40:36,709
You can't say anything while eating this dish.

912
00:40:38,909 --> 00:40:42,549
(Customers of Hohyunghojae are particularly quiet.)

913
00:40:46,689 --> 00:40:47,789
- It's good, right?
- Yes.

914
00:40:48,959 --> 00:40:50,059
Are we on a good pace?

915
00:40:50,359 --> 00:40:51,619
No, we're not.

916
00:40:52,359 --> 00:40:54,559
- Are we backed up?
- Quite a lot.

917
00:40:56,359 --> 00:40:58,259
I wonder how much sales we made.

918
00:41:03,969 --> 00:41:05,039
What's this?

919
00:41:09,579 --> 00:41:10,579
Are you okay?

920
00:41:12,039 --> 00:41:13,049
Yes.

921
00:41:13,879 --> 00:41:15,349
Look at all the orders...

922
00:41:15,419 --> 00:41:17,849
- Chef Jung Ho Young has.
- What?

923
00:41:18,219 --> 00:41:19,919
Chef Jung Ho Young has a lot of orders.

924
00:41:22,049 --> 00:41:24,019
I'm so dead now.

925
00:41:25,789 --> 00:41:28,059
Do we have that many orders right now?

926
00:41:29,629 --> 00:41:32,569
(25 orders came all at once.)

927
00:41:36,269 --> 00:41:39,469
(Hyungjae futomaki meal, 25 orders)

928
00:41:39,569 --> 00:41:42,239
I had a mental breakdown back then. I really did.

929
00:41:42,509 --> 00:41:46,749
Even a professional takes at least 7 to 10 minutes to roll...

930
00:41:47,079 --> 00:41:49,848
one Japanese-style gimbap.

931
00:41:49,849 --> 00:41:53,049
It's a huge roll using two sheets of dried laver.

932
00:41:53,489 --> 00:41:54,489
One futomaki.

933
00:41:55,049 --> 00:41:56,089
Two in total?

934
00:41:56,359 --> 00:41:57,418
Two in total.

935
00:41:57,419 --> 00:41:58,589
How many futomaki?

936
00:42:00,029 --> 00:42:01,589
- Eight.
- Okay, eight.

937
00:42:02,399 --> 00:42:03,458
Eight futomaki.

938
00:42:03,459 --> 00:42:05,299
We'll serve 7 1st, Ho Young.

939
00:42:05,399 --> 00:42:06,569
- Seven.
- Yes.

940
00:42:06,729 --> 00:42:08,169
We're behind orders.

941
00:42:10,169 --> 00:42:11,569
Either way, we're fine.

942
00:42:11,999 --> 00:42:13,009
We're doing fine, Ho Young.

943
00:42:13,669 --> 00:42:16,109
We're fine.

944
00:42:17,609 --> 00:42:18,978
(While getting the orders out amid the chaos)

945
00:42:18,979 --> 00:42:20,679
- We're going to get sick.
- Gosh.

946
00:42:23,019 --> 00:42:25,419
In a competition show like this one,

947
00:42:25,749 --> 00:42:27,149
Chinese cuisine has the upper hand.

948
00:42:27,519 --> 00:42:30,119
The greasy smell of Chinese food.

949
00:42:31,759 --> 00:42:33,129
Customers will get captivated by it.

950
00:42:33,729 --> 00:42:36,159
All the masters of Chinese cuisine are here.

951
00:42:36,459 --> 00:42:38,799
We've got two dangerous teams here.

952
00:42:39,729 --> 00:42:41,798
(The two masters are across from each other.)

953
00:42:41,799 --> 00:42:45,468
The street restaurant to achieve 500 dollars in sales...

954
00:42:45,469 --> 00:42:47,009
is...

955
00:42:47,769 --> 00:42:49,138
Familiar food sells.

956
00:42:49,139 --> 00:42:51,408
Every time I tried selling something...

957
00:42:51,409 --> 00:42:53,649
that's too out there or hard to grasp,

958
00:42:54,109 --> 00:42:55,209
things didn't work out.

959
00:42:55,349 --> 00:42:58,279
Jjajang and jjamppong are everywhere.

960
00:42:58,889 --> 00:43:01,648
We wanted to break away from the cliche.

961
00:43:01,649 --> 00:43:03,689
(Is it Sunlin with a new taste of Chinese cuisine?)

962
00:43:07,089 --> 00:43:08,188
Which way should we go?

963
00:43:08,189 --> 00:43:09,559
Sunlin! Chinese food!

964
00:43:11,159 --> 00:43:12,528
I'll get Chinese food.

965
00:43:12,529 --> 00:43:13,899
(Clearly a Chinese restaurant)

966
00:43:15,639 --> 00:43:17,299
It looks good.

967
00:43:19,139 --> 00:43:20,209
A rice bowl meal?

968
00:43:20,909 --> 00:43:22,169
Mianbao xia.

969
00:43:23,109 --> 00:43:24,538
It does look good.

970
00:43:24,539 --> 00:43:25,749
(Yellow chilli meat rice bowl meal, 15.90 dollars)

971
00:43:26,779 --> 00:43:28,108
Youtiao xia?

972
00:43:28,109 --> 00:43:29,349
(Sunlin)

973
00:43:29,779 --> 00:43:31,879
It's a new version of mianbao xia.

974
00:43:32,489 --> 00:43:34,089
Five-colour bibim jjajang?

975
00:43:34,619 --> 00:43:35,959
That sounds intriguing.

976
00:43:37,789 --> 00:43:38,929
It looks interesting.

977
00:43:40,629 --> 00:43:42,958
- Bibim jjajang.
- That looks good.

978
00:43:42,959 --> 00:43:44,759
(The curious customers start gathering.)

979
00:43:44,799 --> 00:43:46,869
(Sunlin)

980
00:43:47,269 --> 00:43:48,299
We've got an order.

981
00:43:50,169 --> 00:43:51,498
(Clapping)

982
00:43:51,499 --> 00:43:53,608
Two meals. Rice bowl meals.

983
00:43:53,609 --> 00:43:54,909
We're starting with a rice bowl.

984
00:43:55,369 --> 00:43:58,479
Rice bowl meal with youtiao xia.

985
00:43:59,149 --> 00:44:00,149
Here.

986
00:44:00,150 --> 00:44:02,749
(Yellow chilli meat rice bowl)

987
00:44:03,119 --> 00:44:04,349
We've got another order.

988
00:44:06,889 --> 00:44:08,448
It's a type of mianbao xia,

989
00:44:08,449 --> 00:44:09,989
but made with Chinese twisted donuts.

990
00:44:11,059 --> 00:44:12,329
Dad, it's a meal.

991
00:44:12,759 --> 00:44:15,759
(Youtiao xia and yellow chilli meat rice bowl meal)

992
00:44:16,599 --> 00:44:17,928
Was it the chilli rice bowl?

993
00:44:17,929 --> 00:44:20,769
- Is this Chinese food?
- Yes, yellow chilli meat rice bowl.

994
00:44:24,639 --> 00:44:26,568
- Actually...
- Strange. It's a new taste.

995
00:44:26,569 --> 00:44:28,309
- But it's good.
- I've never seen this before.

996
00:44:28,369 --> 00:44:30,579
Is it pickled cucumbers?

997
00:44:31,439 --> 00:44:32,648
It looks like a bulgogi rice bowl.

998
00:44:32,649 --> 00:44:34,549
- No, it tastes nothing like that.
- Is that so?

999
00:44:35,379 --> 00:44:38,179
- It must have jalapenos in it.
- Right?

1000
00:44:38,879 --> 00:44:41,418
- Like a spicy pickle.
- I see.

1001
00:44:41,419 --> 00:44:42,718
So... Right?

1002
00:44:42,719 --> 00:44:44,919
- Isn't it a new taste?
- Totally.

1003
00:44:46,459 --> 00:44:48,189
- It's from a Chinese place, right?
- Yes.

1004
00:44:50,099 --> 00:44:51,328
I've been craving jjajangmyeon...

1005
00:44:51,329 --> 00:44:52,368
- since yesterday.
- Me too.

1006
00:44:52,369 --> 00:44:53,428
Chinese food.

1007
00:44:53,429 --> 00:44:55,329
(The customers are craving jjajangmyeon.)

1008
00:44:59,769 --> 00:45:00,938
(BokBok by Lee Yeon Bok)

1009
00:45:00,939 --> 00:45:02,169
This for now.

1010
00:45:03,539 --> 00:45:05,709
The jjajangmyeon is seven dollars.

1011
00:45:06,549 --> 00:45:07,808
There are two Chinese places.

1012
00:45:07,809 --> 00:45:10,118
- Over here and over there.
- Sunlin?

1013
00:45:10,119 --> 00:45:11,518
(Yoo Bang Nyeong, Five-colour bibim jjajang)

1014
00:45:11,519 --> 00:45:12,649
I want two dishes.

1015
00:45:14,319 --> 00:45:15,389
- Bibim jjajang?
- Are you going to order?

1016
00:45:15,919 --> 00:45:17,288
Should I try the bibim jjajang?

1017
00:45:17,289 --> 00:45:18,489
- I'll get this one.
- Okay.

1018
00:45:20,729 --> 00:45:22,899
(Decided on Sunlin)

1019
00:45:22,959 --> 00:45:25,359
(Five-colour bibim jjajang, 9.50 dollars)

1020
00:45:26,769 --> 00:45:28,099
I ordered jjajangmyeon.

1021
00:45:28,329 --> 00:45:29,399
Five-colour bibim jjajang?

1022
00:45:30,669 --> 00:45:31,769
We've got another order.

1023
00:45:33,209 --> 00:45:35,609
(Onto the rinsed corn noodles)

1024
00:45:35,809 --> 00:45:38,079
(Topping it with 4 kinds of garnishes)

1025
00:45:38,639 --> 00:45:41,449
(Finishing it off with jjajang sauce)

1026
00:45:44,319 --> 00:45:47,419
(Five-colour bibim jjajang, 9.50 dollars)

1027
00:45:47,889 --> 00:45:50,959
(Five-colour bibim jjajang)

1028
00:45:51,419 --> 00:45:53,558
(What do the customers who have been craving jjajangmyeon think?)

1029
00:45:53,559 --> 00:45:54,629
So it's served like this.

1030
00:45:54,989 --> 00:45:57,659
It's five-colour bibim jjajang.

1031
00:45:59,469 --> 00:46:00,999
(Impressed)

1032
00:46:02,999 --> 00:46:04,068
It's cold.

1033
00:46:04,069 --> 00:46:05,269
- What?
- It's cold.

1034
00:46:05,399 --> 00:46:06,609
- Did you say cold?
- Yes.

1035
00:46:07,839 --> 00:46:09,909
This dish is cold.

1036
00:46:12,709 --> 00:46:13,749
Is it cold jjajang?

1037
00:46:13,949 --> 00:46:15,449
Wait, what's this?

1038
00:46:15,779 --> 00:46:17,249
It tastes fine.

1039
00:46:17,679 --> 00:46:18,919
- The jjajangmyeon?
- Yes.

1040
00:46:19,049 --> 00:46:21,289
It's not bad at all. It's good.

1041
00:46:21,749 --> 00:46:23,489
- Can I try your jjajangmyeon?
- Go ahead.

1042
00:46:24,419 --> 00:46:25,858
- You should have a taste.
- Apparently, it's cold.

1043
00:46:25,859 --> 00:46:26,889
It is cold.

1044
00:46:32,999 --> 00:46:35,329
The noodles themselves aren't bad.

1045
00:46:35,569 --> 00:46:37,769
(Surprised)

1046
00:46:38,669 --> 00:46:40,638
- Was this bibim jjajang?
- Yes.

1047
00:46:40,639 --> 00:46:43,079
We should think of it as bibim noodles.

1048
00:46:43,239 --> 00:46:44,708
- Is that so?
- Aren't bibim noodles served cold?

1049
00:46:44,709 --> 00:46:45,749
It is.

1050
00:46:46,649 --> 00:46:48,708
