1068
00:47:37,599 --> 00:47:39,329
Two jjajang, two jjamppong.

1069
00:47:39,929 --> 00:47:41,968
(BokBok by Lee Yeon Bok)

1070
00:47:41,969 --> 00:47:44,569
(Beef loin and shrimp jjamppong, 12 dollars)

1071
00:47:47,669 --> 00:47:50,479
(Freshwater snail jjajangmyeon, 7 dollars)

1072
00:47:54,709 --> 00:47:55,818
I'm digging in.

1073
00:47:55,819 --> 00:47:57,018
(Freshwater snail jjajangmyeon, Beef loin and shrimp jjamppong)

1074
00:47:57,019 --> 00:47:58,749
Bon appetit.

1075
00:48:08,289 --> 00:48:09,959
(Laughing)

1076
00:48:11,129 --> 00:48:12,159
It's good.

1077
00:48:14,829 --> 00:48:15,969
It's delicious.

1078
00:48:21,839 --> 00:48:23,709
(Amazed)

1079
00:48:24,179 --> 00:48:26,279
The freshwater snail adds a nice chewy bite.

1080
00:48:28,179 --> 00:48:30,719
It's been a while since I last had good jjajang.

1081
00:48:36,019 --> 00:48:37,419
(Impressed)

1082
00:48:39,119 --> 00:48:40,229
Great.

1083
00:48:41,359 --> 00:48:42,829
I should've had some drinks last night.

1084
00:48:43,899 --> 00:48:46,568
