1202
00:53:33,489 --> 00:53:35,019
Okay, let's do this.

1203
00:53:35,689 --> 00:53:36,889
I'll plate the fried rice.

1204
00:53:47,399 --> 00:53:48,669
Okay, all set.

1205
00:53:49,499 --> 00:53:52,169
(Onions, green onions, and red quinoa garnishes)

1206
00:53:52,669 --> 00:53:54,839
(Handmade mayo sauce)

1207
00:53:55,639 --> 00:53:58,779
(Handmade chilli sauce, deep-fried shrimp)

1208
00:53:59,609 --> 00:54:00,749
Five shrimps.

1209
00:54:02,779 --> 00:54:05,019
Number 8581. Yes, here it is.

1210
00:54:06,549 --> 00:54:08,619
Number 4505. Okay.

1211
00:54:09,289 --> 00:54:10,419
Enjoy.

1212
00:54:11,089 --> 00:54:12,089
Thank you.

1213
00:54:12,090 --> 00:54:15,159
(The male customers are waiting.)

1214
00:54:23,439 --> 00:54:26,269
(Kkanpunggi chicken over rice)

1215
00:54:26,909 --> 00:54:28,309
- It's good.
- The shrimp is good.

1216
00:54:37,379 --> 00:54:39,478
Very nice. Thanks, Chef Hong.

1217
00:54:39,479 --> 00:54:41,219
- Nice.
- Nice.

1218
00:54:42,619 --> 00:54:44,619
I hope the customers are like, "How pretty!" when they see it.

1219
00:54:45,189 --> 00:54:47,158
- Did they?
- No, I hope they do.

1220
00:54:47,159 --> 00:54:48,189
Come on.

1221
00:54:49,059 --> 00:54:50,259
Thank you for the meal.

1222
00:54:51,129 --> 00:54:52,929
- Look.
- Like this?

1223
00:54:53,229 --> 00:54:54,928
- It's really pretty.
- How pretty.

1224
00:54:54,929 --> 00:54:55,929
Right?

1225
00:54:55,930 --> 00:54:57,139
What's this?

1226
00:54:59,099 --> 00:55:00,209
I'm curious.

1227
00:55:01,369 --> 00:55:02,439
Push this down.

1228
00:55:04,379 --> 00:55:05,439
It's good.

1229
00:55:05,779 --> 00:55:07,309
This is good.

1230
00:55:08,049 --> 00:55:09,378
- Is it bread?
- It's not mianbao xia.

1231
00:55:09,379 --> 00:55:11,579
- Yes, it seems like it.
- It looks amazing.

1232
00:55:13,849 --> 00:55:15,749
(Crunchy)

1233
00:55:17,259 --> 00:55:18,688
(Surprised)

1234
00:55:18,689 --> 00:55:19,789
What is it? Is it good?

1235
00:55:20,329 --> 00:55:21,859
- Is it different?
- Yes.

1236
00:55:23,829 --> 00:55:24,899
Try it.

1237
00:55:27,169 --> 00:55:28,428
(Shocked)

1238
00:55:28,429 --> 00:55:30,339
- It's amazing.
- It's delicious.

1239
00:55:32,139 --> 00:55:33,708
It's Korean if you have it with dried laver,

1240
00:55:33,709 --> 00:55:36,479
and a dessert if you have it...

1241
00:55:36,979 --> 00:55:38,008
- It's crunchy.
- with bread.

1242
00:55:38,009 --> 00:55:39,009
Right?

1243
00:55:39,979 --> 00:55:42,278
This is really good. I'm shocked.

1244
00:55:42,279 --> 00:55:43,379
It's amazing.

1245
00:55:44,619 --> 00:55:46,219
(Glancing)

1246
00:55:46,289 --> 00:55:48,619
We're doing great. The other places don't have any orders.

1247
00:55:49,959 --> 00:55:51,159
It's going smoothly.

1248
00:55:52,359 --> 00:55:54,228
(Ma Restaurant)

1249
00:55:54,229 --> 00:55:57,599
(Goal!)

1250
00:55:58,129 --> 00:56:02,099
(Edward Kwon has some time to kill now.)

1251
00:56:02,599 --> 00:56:05,969
My plan is to take away Edward's customers.

1252
00:56:07,369 --> 00:56:08,839
Kkanpunggi...

1253
00:56:09,509 --> 00:56:10,678
Kkanpunggi chicken.

1254
00:56:10,679 --> 00:56:14,509
(Ma Restaurant by Edward Kwon)

1255
00:56:15,279 --> 00:56:16,578
That one looks good.

1256
00:56:16,579 --> 00:56:18,248
(Goal! by Hong Seok Cheon)

1257
00:56:18,249 --> 00:56:21,289
(Goal!, Ma Restaurant)

1258
00:56:32,199 --> 00:56:33,768
Alaskan pink shrimp avocado tartare.

1259
00:56:33,769 --> 00:56:36,168
(The female customers have passed by Ma Restaurant.)

1260
00:56:36,169 --> 00:56:38,698
The street restaurant to achieve 500 dollars in sales...

1261
00:56:38,699 --> 00:56:39,868
(Jo Seo Hyung, Kim Mi Ryeong,)

1262
00:56:39,869 --> 00:56:41,238
(Kim Hoon, Jung Ho Young, Lee Yeon Bok)

1263
00:56:41,239 --> 00:56:42,408
is Hong Seok Cheon.

1264
00:56:42,409 --> 00:56:43,708
(Jo Seo Hyung, Kim Mi Ryeong,)

1265
00:56:43,709 --> 00:56:45,609
(Kim Hoon, Jung Ho Young, Lee Yeon Bok, Hong Seok Cheon)

1266
00:56:47,549 --> 00:56:48,549
Number 3374.

1267
00:56:49,109 --> 00:56:50,119
Number 0788.

1268
00:56:50,419 --> 00:56:52,349
Call number 2198.

1269
00:56:52,919 --> 00:56:54,418
Grand slam, number 7309.

1270
00:56:54,419 --> 00:56:55,489
Number 7309.

1271
00:56:55,889 --> 00:56:57,788
Tell me if it's ready.

1272
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:58,858
Okay.

1273
00:56:58,859 --> 00:57:01,428
There are many chefs who make such fine dishes,

1274
00:57:01,429 --> 00:57:03,198
but would they bother making something like a soup?

1275
00:57:03,199 --> 00:57:05,198
When you look at fine dining chefs,

1276
00:57:05,199 --> 00:57:07,029
you know that those dishes don't sell well.

1277
00:57:07,269 --> 00:57:09,798
I wonder how a chef like Lim Ki Hak, who has only done fine dining,

1278
00:57:09,799 --> 00:57:13,239
is going to pull off a street food business.

1279
00:57:14,109 --> 00:57:17,138
Although I find dishes that are made slowly over a long time...

1280
00:57:17,139 --> 00:57:19,678
more attractive than something...

1281
00:57:19,679 --> 00:57:21,449
that has to be whipped up quickly,

1282
00:57:21,509 --> 00:57:24,278
to be honest, when I'm supposed...

1283
00:57:24,279 --> 00:57:27,188
to pile things into a single bowl...

1284
00:57:27,189 --> 00:57:28,389
and serve it...

1285
00:57:28,489 --> 00:57:29,889
as soon as possible,

1286
00:57:30,859 --> 00:57:32,259
it actually excites me.

1287
00:57:34,529 --> 00:57:36,729
The main dish is called poulet basquaise.

1288
00:57:37,459 --> 00:57:40,868
I wanted to serve it with a sausage.

1289
00:57:40,869 --> 00:57:43,538
To give it the feel of a course meal,

1290
00:57:43,539 --> 00:57:46,569
I put things together and named it Grand Slam.

1291
00:57:47,409 --> 00:57:50,578
Since we have to serve a set amount within a set time anyway,

1292
00:57:50,579 --> 00:57:51,579
Okay.

1293
00:57:51,580 --> 00:57:54,608
my plan is to do the prep work hard in advance.

1294
00:57:54,609 --> 00:57:55,648
All right.

1295
00:57:55,649 --> 00:57:57,149
It will be a gukbap-restaurant style.

1296
00:57:57,849 --> 00:57:59,249
We just scoop it out and serve it right away.

1297
00:57:59,379 --> 00:58:00,548
Okay.

1298
00:58:00,549 --> 00:58:02,788
(A meeting of a French course meal and a gukbap-restaurant system)

1299
00:58:02,789 --> 00:58:06,829
(1. Ladle the stew over the pre-scooped rice.)

1300
00:58:09,929 --> 00:58:12,659
(2. Top it with the grilled sausage.)

1301
00:58:17,639 --> 00:58:20,539
(3. Plate the pre-made dessert.)

1302
00:58:24,609 --> 00:58:25,678
It's done.

1303
00:58:25,679 --> 00:58:26,778
(The time it takes to serve one full set...)

1304
00:58:26,779 --> 00:58:29,649
(is only 1 minute.)

1305
00:58:31,779 --> 00:58:33,348
- I bet this is delicious.
- A can and ice.

1306
00:58:33,349 --> 00:58:34,988
A spicy sausage and creme caramel.

1307
00:58:34,989 --> 00:58:36,289
- It sounds pretty good.
- Yes.

1308
00:58:36,519 --> 00:58:38,689
Let's try this. This place looks good.

1309
00:58:39,189 --> 00:58:40,229
It must be delicious.

1310
00:58:40,889 --> 00:58:42,689
- It sounds great.
- I bet it's good.

1311
00:58:43,299 --> 00:58:44,898
It's only 4.5 dollars. That's cheap.

1312
00:58:44,899 --> 00:58:45,998
(The line suddenly grew so long.)

1313
00:58:45,999 --> 00:58:47,768
Hang on a second. Now...

1314
00:58:47,769 --> 00:58:49,068
Wait. We have to do something.

1315
00:58:49,069 --> 00:58:50,199
Okay.

1316
00:58:51,239 --> 00:58:53,338
The order sheets kept piling up,

1317
00:58:53,339 --> 00:58:54,809
but there was no place to even put them.

1318
00:58:56,409 --> 00:58:58,938
I felt like we'd be in huge trouble if we didn't fix it...

1319
00:58:58,939 --> 00:59:00,049
quickly somehow.

1320
00:59:00,249 --> 00:59:02,008
- One of these.
- This is driving me crazy.

1321
00:59:02,009 --> 00:59:03,249
We don't know how many of them were served, right?

1322
00:59:03,949 --> 00:59:06,948
Using two copies makes it too complicated.

1323
00:59:06,949 --> 00:59:09,449
Let's just check this screen and this order sheet.

1324
00:59:10,789 --> 00:59:12,559
- Okay.
- Don't look at the order rack.

1325
00:59:13,459 --> 00:59:15,858
I'll look at the screen and call out the orders for you.

1326
00:59:15,859 --> 00:59:16,859
Okay.

1327
00:59:17,559 --> 00:59:19,969
From now on, only go by what I call out.

1328
00:59:20,029 --> 00:59:21,069
I will.

1329
00:59:21,299 --> 00:59:23,369
Grand Slam, one.

1330
00:59:23,569 --> 00:59:24,668
(In charge of orders)

1331
00:59:24,669 --> 00:59:26,368
- Do we have anything ready?
- Number 6518.

1332
00:59:26,369 --> 00:59:27,768
That's what I just pressed, right?

1333
00:59:27,769 --> 00:59:28,769
Yes.

1334
00:59:28,770 --> 00:59:29,909
Grand Slam, one.

1335
00:59:33,109 --> 00:59:34,509
Number 3797.

1336
00:59:35,879 --> 00:59:37,749
One more. Creme caramel.

1337
00:59:40,689 --> 00:59:42,289
Number 8749.

1338
00:59:42,549 --> 00:59:44,588
- One poulet basquaise.
- Call number 6518.

1339
00:59:44,589 --> 00:59:45,688
Number 6518.

1340
00:59:45,689 --> 00:59:47,188
- One Grand Slam.
- Two poulets basquaise.

1341
00:59:47,189 --> 00:59:48,288
And...

1342
00:59:48,289 --> 00:59:49,628
The small keypad shows...

1343
00:59:49,629 --> 00:59:51,359
how many minutes have passed since the order was placed.

1344
00:59:51,499 --> 00:59:53,098
Even when orders piled up,

1345
00:59:53,099 --> 00:59:55,299
no table had to wait for more than six minutes.

1346
00:59:55,499 --> 00:59:56,699
Please enjoy your food.

1347
00:59:57,739 --> 00:59:58,868
Okay. Next.

1348
00:59:58,869 --> 00:59:59,939
Please enjoy your food.

1349
00:59:59,969 --> 01:00:01,209
It's creme caramel.

1350
01:00:01,939 --> 01:00:02,969
Please enjoy your food.

1351
01:00:13,489 --> 01:00:15,148
(Exclaiming)

1352
01:00:15,149 --> 01:00:16,289
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

1353
01:00:16,959 --> 01:00:18,059
Really?

1354
01:00:18,589 --> 01:00:20,129
- This is so good.
- Can you taste the spices?

1355
01:00:21,029 --> 01:00:22,059
But it's not too strong.

1356
01:00:23,329 --> 01:00:24,799
- You're right.
- And it's served fast.

1357
01:00:24,899 --> 01:00:26,669
I got this as soon as I ordered it.

1358
01:00:28,229 --> 01:00:30,269
(After payment,)

1359
01:00:33,909 --> 01:00:36,678
(she picked up the food only in 53 seconds.)

1360
01:00:36,679 --> 01:00:38,279
And the food is pretty good.

1361
01:00:43,979 --> 01:00:45,549
This is delicious.

1362
01:00:46,549 --> 01:00:47,819
Is this a French dish?

1363
01:00:48,449 --> 01:00:50,289
How does it taste? Do you find it familiar?

1364
01:00:50,559 --> 01:00:51,589
No.

1365
01:00:52,189 --> 01:00:53,528
It's something like a stew.

1366
01:00:53,529 --> 01:00:54,789
- A tomato flavour?
- Yes.

1367
01:00:55,559 --> 01:00:56,958
It doesn't taste like a store-bought sauce.

1368
01:00:56,959 --> 01:00:59,858
It's like they actually simmered real tomatoes to make it.

1369
01:00:59,859 --> 01:01:01,129
It's definitely not the flavour of a commercial product.

1370
01:01:01,229 --> 01:01:03,398
It's a French dish, but it has a spicy aftertaste.

1371
01:01:03,399 --> 01:01:04,838
I think Koreans will love it.

1372
01:01:04,839 --> 01:01:07,369
The sausage is really good.

1373
01:01:07,539 --> 01:01:09,269
It has a subtle hint of chilli aroma.

1374
01:01:09,839 --> 01:01:13,278
I think the authentic French flavour really hits you in the dessert.

1375
01:01:13,279 --> 01:01:14,409
- Really?
- This is no joke.

1376
01:01:15,309 --> 01:01:16,649
I bet that's why it's served as a set.

1377
01:01:19,179 --> 01:01:22,449
I think this is the best one in terms of value for money.

1378
01:01:22,689 --> 01:01:25,789
We believe our dish is highly differentiated.

1379
01:01:25,959 --> 01:01:27,988
The main dish is poulet basquaise,

1380
01:01:27,989 --> 01:01:29,998
and it's served with a Basque-style sausage on the side.

1381
01:01:29,999 --> 01:01:31,028
And we have a dessert.

1382
01:01:31,029 --> 01:01:33,098
I thought it would be worth a shot...

1383
01:01:33,099 --> 01:01:35,628
if we could deliver authentic French flavours...

1384
01:01:35,629 --> 01:01:37,039
at a low price point.

1385
01:01:37,539 --> 01:01:39,638
Three Grand Slams and one creme caramel.

1386
01:01:39,639 --> 01:01:42,569
(Current Revenue of Bol A Bol: 590.13 dollars)

1387
01:01:47,249 --> 01:01:49,078
We have the first surviving restaurant...

1388
01:01:49,079 --> 01:01:51,979
of the 1,000 dollar sales race.

1389
01:01:53,079 --> 01:01:54,149
I bet there's another survivor.

1390
01:01:54,549 --> 01:01:55,589
Who is it?

1391
01:01:56,659 --> 01:01:58,589
The first restaurant to survive is...

1392
01:01:59,459 --> 01:02:00,628
One raw fish guksu.

1393
01:02:00,629 --> 01:02:01,728
One raw fish guksu.

1394
01:02:01,729 --> 01:02:03,799
Please keep cutting that if you can do that.

1395
01:02:03,859 --> 01:02:05,459
Why is our food so popular?

1396
01:02:06,129 --> 01:02:07,598
Hey, we got a lot of orders now.

1397
01:02:07,599 --> 01:02:08,829
Just keep making it, okay?

1398
01:02:08,869 --> 01:02:10,639
There are a lot of orders of Grand Slam.

1399
01:02:10,739 --> 01:02:12,969
Let's hurry and reach 1,000 dollars during lunch.

1400
01:02:13,409 --> 01:02:15,608
The first restaurant to survive is...

1401
01:02:15,609 --> 01:02:18,879
(The first surviving restaurant)

1402
01:02:20,574 --> 01:02:21,973
The Sauce.

1403
01:02:21,974 --> 01:02:24,203
(The Sauce by Choi Sang Hyun)

1404
01:02:24,204 --> 01:02:25,513
The Sauce.

1405
01:02:25,514 --> 01:02:26,743
- The Sauce?
- Which one?

1406
01:02:26,744 --> 01:02:28,283
- The Sauce?
- The Sauce?

1407
01:02:28,284 --> 01:02:29,484
What is it again?

1408
01:02:30,044 --> 01:02:32,184
- The Sauce.
- Nice.

1409
01:02:32,614 --> 01:02:34,654
Okay. We've survived.

1410
01:02:34,984 --> 01:02:36,184
Nice.

1411
01:02:36,354 --> 01:02:37,784
We weren't getting any orders.

1412
01:02:38,294 --> 01:02:39,624
The fresh pasta?

1413
01:02:41,364 --> 01:02:43,124
He survived with the fresh pasta.

1414
01:02:43,864 --> 01:02:45,794
- How did he do it?
- I know.

1415
01:02:46,494 --> 01:02:47,933
I think the waiting line...

1416
01:02:47,934 --> 01:02:49,164
played a huge part.

1417
01:02:49,734 --> 01:02:50,763
When we had the payment problem.

1418
01:02:50,764 --> 01:02:51,773
(What's the secret behind the number 1 survivor?)

1419
01:02:51,774 --> 01:02:53,304
Our POS system wasn't working at first.

1420
01:02:53,374 --> 01:02:55,544
I thought we'd be in huge trouble.

1421
01:02:56,404 --> 01:02:58,074
- Why doesn't it work?
- Why? Does it not work?

1422
01:02:58,414 --> 01:03:01,814
But it actually made people line up,

1423
01:03:02,084 --> 01:03:04,184
which seemed to attract more customers.

1424
01:03:07,184 --> 01:03:08,424
More people have come.

1425
01:03:09,284 --> 01:03:11,124
This place is really popular.

1426
01:03:11,354 --> 01:03:13,693
I'm curious about the pasta, but the line is just too long.

1427
01:03:13,694 --> 01:03:15,423
I was going to eat it if possible,

1428
01:03:15,424 --> 01:03:16,424
but it's not easy.

1429
01:03:17,194 --> 01:03:18,833
I'm curious about the fresh pasta.

1430
01:03:18,834 --> 01:03:20,463
I'm really curious about it.

1431
01:03:20,464 --> 01:03:22,904
I would've tried it if the line hadn't been this long.

1432
01:03:24,334 --> 01:03:26,833
- There's a line at The Sauce.
- It's a popular restaurant now.

1433
01:03:26,834 --> 01:03:27,933
It's become a restaurant worth waiting for.

1434
01:03:27,934 --> 01:03:30,644
(The Sauce became a restaurant with a long waiting line.)

1435
01:03:31,044 --> 01:03:32,144
We're getting a lot of ice cream orders.

1436
01:03:32,744 --> 01:03:34,114
Seung Jae, we're getting too many ice cream orders.

1437
01:03:34,944 --> 01:03:36,913
- The ice cream is selling well.
- I know.

1438
01:03:36,914 --> 01:03:38,254
It must be because of the hot weather.

1439
01:03:39,314 --> 01:03:42,154
(Another secret to survival is the weather.)

1440
01:03:42,384 --> 01:03:44,484
I never expected the sunlight to be this intense.

1441
01:03:44,954 --> 01:03:47,124
The sunlight is the real wild card here.

1442
01:03:47,224 --> 01:03:48,624
That's true.

1443
01:03:50,194 --> 01:03:52,534
I went out to write down the menu and origins,

1444
01:03:52,634 --> 01:03:55,604
but then it suddenly started getting so hot.

1445
01:03:57,634 --> 01:03:59,833
Since the dining area was out in the plaza,

1446
01:03:59,834 --> 01:04:01,034
the sunlight was just too intense.

1447
01:04:07,844 --> 01:04:11,083
It crossed my mind that ice cream might actually sell...

1448
01:04:11,084 --> 01:04:12,654
really well.

1449
01:04:13,884 --> 01:04:15,953
Could we add one item to our POS system?

1450
01:04:15,954 --> 01:04:17,854
We want to add one more ice cream menu.

1451
01:04:19,154 --> 01:04:21,193
If it's okay, I will write it down on the board.

1452
01:04:21,194 --> 01:04:22,223
(He decided to add a menu item on the spot.)

1453
01:04:22,224 --> 01:04:24,523
The ice cream base was the same anyway.

1454
01:04:24,524 --> 01:04:27,163
I remembered the perilla oil I had ordered just in case,

1455
01:04:27,164 --> 01:04:28,533
so I added the menu,

1456
01:04:28,534 --> 01:04:30,203
perilla oil ice cream on the spot.

1457
01:04:30,204 --> 01:04:31,234
(Perilla oil ice cream is added.)

1458
01:04:31,534 --> 01:04:33,604
We can make perilla oil ice cream.

1459
01:04:33,904 --> 01:04:35,573
But we didn't have time to take a picture of it.

1460
01:04:35,574 --> 01:04:36,674
Since we didn't have a picture,

1461
01:04:37,744 --> 01:04:38,773
we made it a hidden menu item.

1462
01:04:38,774 --> 01:04:41,914
(Limited offer, a hidden menu item)

1463
01:04:42,314 --> 01:04:43,343
(Olive gelato)

1464
01:04:43,344 --> 01:04:45,184
(Olive oil, black olive candy, freeze-dried tangerine chips)

1465
01:04:45,614 --> 01:04:46,913
(Only perilla oil gelato)

1466
01:04:46,914 --> 01:04:48,224
(Perilla oil)

1467
01:04:48,554 --> 01:04:50,583
People are lining up over there at the ice cream place.

1468
01:04:50,584 --> 01:04:52,054
- I see.
- Because it's hot.

1469
01:04:52,424 --> 01:04:54,764
- They have ice cream on the menu?
- Yes.

1470
01:04:56,464 --> 01:04:57,824
I want to eat something cool.

1471
01:04:58,394 --> 01:04:59,994
Ice cream would be perfect right now.

1472
01:05:01,504 --> 01:05:03,203
Let's try something a bit more unique.

1473
01:05:03,204 --> 01:05:04,934
- The perilla oil one?
- I like it.

1474
01:05:06,004 --> 01:05:07,433
Let's order both.

1475
01:05:07,434 --> 01:05:09,373
Okay. The olive gelato and...

1476
01:05:09,374 --> 01:05:11,004
We're getting a lot of ice cream orders.

1477
01:05:11,374 --> 01:05:12,374
I'm just grateful.

1478
01:05:13,374 --> 01:05:16,213
The ticket machine kept buzzing and spitting out order sheets,

1479
01:05:16,214 --> 01:05:17,413
Keep going, Seung Jae.

1480
01:05:17,414 --> 01:05:18,854
so I just had to make a quick call.

1481
01:05:18,914 --> 01:05:20,413
Since the pasta was the main dish...

1482
01:05:20,414 --> 01:05:22,153
and the ice cream was a side anyway,

1483
01:05:22,154 --> 01:05:24,523
Seung Jae kept cooking the pasta...

1484
01:05:24,524 --> 01:05:26,824
while I focused on scooping out the ice cream.

1485
01:05:27,594 --> 01:05:28,923
We just served them 1 by 1...

1486
01:05:28,924 --> 01:05:31,224
in the order they came in on the POS system.

1487
01:05:31,834 --> 01:05:34,034
If you only ordered pasta, you can come and pick up your food.

1488
01:05:38,234 --> 01:05:39,673
I ordered ice cream with it.

1489
01:05:39,674 --> 01:05:41,073
- Did you order olive gelato?
- Yes.

1490
01:05:41,074 --> 01:05:42,074
Here you are.

1491
01:05:42,574 --> 01:05:44,174
I'm going to try the gelato.

1492
01:05:44,674 --> 01:05:46,774
(The waiting line draws in more customers.)

1493
01:05:47,674 --> 01:05:49,114
Seung Jae, keep going.

1494
01:05:50,644 --> 01:05:52,214
Order sheets are pouring in.

1495
01:05:53,114 --> 01:05:55,084
- Four.
- Four.

1496
01:05:55,224 --> 01:05:56,854
And three pasta dishes each.

1497
01:05:57,424 --> 01:06:00,254
(Rapidly piling up revenue)

1498
01:06:00,854 --> 01:06:02,324
- It's for this one.
- Marinated shrimp.

1499
01:06:02,464 --> 01:06:03,624
I'll go first.

1500
01:06:03,824 --> 01:06:05,263
So many orders of Korean calcot. It's driving me crazy.

1501
01:06:05,264 --> 01:06:07,134
- One jjamppong.
- Two Grand Slam.

1502
01:06:07,494 --> 01:06:08,934
- One raw fish guksu.
- Okay.

1503
01:06:08,964 --> 01:06:10,633
Something isn't working.

1504
01:06:10,634 --> 01:06:11,933
Something's wrong. Help me.

1505
01:06:11,934 --> 01:06:12,934
(Choi Sang Hyun: A glitch in the POS system)

1506
01:06:13,074 --> 01:06:14,634
I'll start cooking the noodles.

1507
01:06:15,044 --> 01:06:17,174
We just have to keep going. Orders are flooding in.

1508
01:06:17,574 --> 01:06:19,143
Just keep going with no break.

1509
01:06:19,144 --> 01:06:21,913
(After 30 minutes later, Team Choi Sang Hyun...)

1510
01:06:21,914 --> 01:06:23,713
(could resume taking the orders.)

1511
01:06:23,714 --> 01:06:25,483
(The refund was occurred in Team Jo Seo Hyung.)

1512
01:06:25,484 --> 01:06:27,184
Seung Jae, we're almost out of ice cream.

1513
01:06:27,454 --> 01:06:28,484
Let's wrap it up during lunchtime.

1514
01:06:28,954 --> 01:06:30,554
Who ordered ice cream?

1515
01:06:30,724 --> 01:06:34,253
(They became the 1st to survive 45 minutes after resuming orders.)

1516
01:06:34,254 --> 01:06:35,294
Nice.

1517
01:06:35,364 --> 01:06:37,464
I panicked when no orders were coming in.

1518
01:06:37,694 --> 01:06:40,494
I think having a single menu item and ice cream worked out well.

1519
01:06:41,034 --> 01:06:42,564
I think we've sold over 100 servings of ice cream.

1520
01:06:42,864 --> 01:06:44,934
Ice cream was the best option.

1521
01:06:45,134 --> 01:06:48,073
And adding the perilla oil option was a stroke of genius.

1522
01:06:48,074 --> 01:06:49,444
It was a nice choice to add one more item.

1523
01:06:50,244 --> 01:06:51,914
Ice cream did all the work.

1524
01:06:52,374 --> 01:06:54,174
- I was so happy.
- I'm grateful.

1525
01:06:54,314 --> 01:06:55,344
Thumbs-up.

1526
01:06:56,984 --> 01:06:58,014
Seung Jae.

1527
01:07:02,554 --> 01:07:03,853
We did it. We've survived.

1528
01:07:03,854 --> 01:07:05,423
(1st place: The Sauce with 1,118.5 dollars)

1529
01:07:05,424 --> 01:07:06,994
(50 plates of pasta, 110 plates of ice cream)

1530
01:07:07,224 --> 01:07:08,623
What is this yellow thing?

1531
01:07:08,624 --> 01:07:09,664
(Olive gelato, perilla oil gelato)

1532
01:07:10,294 --> 01:07:12,034
Oil? Is it olive oil?

1533
01:07:14,794 --> 01:07:17,204
(1 gelato per person)

1534
01:07:18,064 --> 01:07:20,533
Why do perilla oil and ice cream go so well together?

1535
01:07:20,534 --> 01:07:21,544
I know.

1536
01:07:21,904 --> 01:07:23,973
The moment you put it in your mouth, the aroma of the perilla oil...

1537
01:07:23,974 --> 01:07:25,413
makes it feel like you're eating a dish.

1538
01:07:25,414 --> 01:07:26,673
But as you keep chewing,

1539
01:07:26,674 --> 01:07:27,943
- it's just gelato.
- It's like ice cream.

1540
01:07:27,944 --> 01:07:30,514
What is this? The crunchy powder is so good.

1541
01:07:31,184 --> 01:07:33,554
- I have no idea what this is.
- Is it some kind of candy?

1542
01:07:34,514 --> 01:07:36,454
(Black olive candy)

1543
01:07:36,854 --> 01:07:39,324
(Freeze-dried tangerine chips)

1544
01:07:42,724 --> 01:07:46,464
It feels like they crushed up something freeze-dried.

1545
01:07:47,194 --> 01:07:48,334
It's so crunchy.

1546
01:07:48,604 --> 01:07:50,033
This crunchy texture works well...

1547
01:07:50,034 --> 01:07:51,234
- as a topping.
- I know.

1548
01:07:51,974 --> 01:07:56,544
(1 hour and 20 minutes into business)

1549
01:07:56,744 --> 01:07:57,744
Orders are flooding in.

1550
01:07:58,914 --> 01:07:59,943
This is crazy.

1551
01:07:59,944 --> 01:08:02,914
- I know. It's going well.
- I bet we're the busiest.

1552
01:08:03,044 --> 01:08:05,154
- Do we need to sell 60 servings?
- Yes, 60 servings.

1553
01:08:05,284 --> 01:08:07,684
If things go well, we can finish it during lunchtime.

1554
01:08:08,854 --> 01:08:10,383
I feel like we've sold about 5,000 dollars worth of food.

1555
01:08:10,384 --> 01:08:12,524
(HunGry: 556.34 dollars)

1556
01:08:12,694 --> 01:08:14,353
Have we not even hit 500 dollars in sales yet?

1557
01:08:14,354 --> 01:08:15,964
I bet we've made at least 500 dollars.

1558
01:08:16,394 --> 01:08:18,563
- Another order for Grand Slam.
- Okay.

1559
01:08:18,564 --> 01:08:21,803
(Goal!: 532.4 dollars, Ma Restaurant: 404.34 dollars)

1560
01:08:21,804 --> 01:08:24,704
(The Sauce: Survived)

1561
01:08:27,834 --> 01:08:30,503
The restaurant with the lowest sales...

1562
01:08:30,504 --> 01:08:32,914
- Who is it?
- is at 47 dollars.

1563
01:08:33,014 --> 01:08:34,374
- My goodness.
- That's just too much.

1564
01:08:35,014 --> 01:08:36,313
(Surprised)

1565
01:08:36,314 --> 01:08:37,344
Which restaurant is it?

1566
01:08:37,514 --> 01:08:38,884
What? Who is it?

1567
01:08:39,414 --> 01:08:41,014
It's only 47 dollars?

1568
01:08:41,514 --> 01:08:42,754
Which restaurant is it?

1569
01:08:43,024 --> 01:08:45,054
- Oh, dear.
- My goodness.

1570
01:08:45,194 --> 01:08:46,854
I feel so bad for them.

1571
01:08:47,554 --> 01:08:48,594
It's only about 40 dollars?

1572
01:08:48,964 --> 01:08:49,964
Where is it?

1573
01:08:50,364 --> 01:08:51,494
Is it Seok Hyun?

1574
01:08:52,494 --> 01:08:53,564
Is it us?

1575
01:08:56,164 --> 01:08:57,164
I bet it's us.

1576
01:08:59,404 --> 01:09:02,074
(Checking the sales)

1577
01:09:05,174 --> 01:09:06,743
I can't go home like this.

1578
01:09:06,744 --> 01:09:08,174
I can't finish in last place.

1579
01:09:08,914 --> 01:09:12,554
Our franchise owners are watching.

1580
01:09:13,684 --> 01:09:16,453
Hello. I started my business with Gochujang Jjigae,

1581
01:09:16,454 --> 01:09:18,694
and now I'm managing 11 different brands.

1582
01:09:18,824 --> 01:09:19,993
My name is Go Seok Hyun.

1583
01:09:19,994 --> 01:09:21,194
(Go Seok Hyun, the CEO of 11 brands)

1584
01:09:21,554 --> 01:09:22,864
You need to listen carefully.

1585
01:09:23,494 --> 01:09:25,564
I'm running Mr. Go's Gochujang Jjigae.

1586
01:09:25,964 --> 01:09:27,764
There are also Yangmun, a beef rib restaurant,

1587
01:09:27,894 --> 01:09:29,663
Daeyeop, Cheonha Jeil Sotttukkeong,

1588
01:09:29,664 --> 01:09:31,504
Bangasil, Whitturu,

1589
01:09:31,804 --> 01:09:33,474
Eussara, Ttukdak...

1590
01:09:33,804 --> 01:09:34,904
How many did I say?

1591
01:09:36,304 --> 01:09:37,403
(The CEO of countless brands)

1592
01:09:37,404 --> 01:09:39,374
How many were they? Did I mention nine brands?

1593
01:09:39,444 --> 01:09:40,613
(Sales Gangster)

1594
01:09:40,614 --> 01:09:42,144
- Sales Gangster.
- Annual sales of 10 million.

1595
01:09:42,484 --> 01:09:44,084
The young boss of Yangmun.

1596
01:09:44,414 --> 01:09:45,953
- My goodness.
- Yangmun.

1597
01:09:45,954 --> 01:09:47,083
Yes, CEO Go Seok Hyun.

1598
01:09:47,084 --> 01:09:48,984
The competition is way more fierce than I expected.

1599
01:09:49,584 --> 01:09:52,293
We've been seeing upward growth year after year.

1600
01:09:52,294 --> 01:09:55,964
And we expect to close this year with 10 million dollars in sales.

1601
01:09:58,294 --> 01:10:02,104
I started this business because I love eating so much.

1602
01:10:02,234 --> 01:10:04,104
It might sound a bit subjective,

1603
01:10:04,564 --> 01:10:07,304
but I only make food that I could eat at least twice a week.

1604
01:10:08,504 --> 01:10:10,873
We have two menu items.

1605
01:10:10,874 --> 01:10:13,474
They are SVT and TVT.

1606
01:10:14,144 --> 01:10:16,614
SVT is spicy vermicelli tteok...

1607
01:10:17,084 --> 01:10:20,054
and TVT is toowoomba sauce vermicelli tteok.

1608
01:10:20,754 --> 01:10:23,183
The restaurant with the lowest sales...

1609
01:10:23,184 --> 01:10:28,764
(The restaurant with 47 dollars in sales is Agungi.)

1610
01:10:29,294 --> 01:10:31,194
The market is right here, but we're the ones failing.

1611
01:10:32,364 --> 01:10:33,494
What should we do?

1612
01:10:36,934 --> 01:10:38,164
The other restaurants are busy.

1613
01:10:38,774 --> 01:10:39,934
They look very busy.

1614
01:10:46,714 --> 01:10:48,314
(Quiet)

1615
01:10:48,714 --> 01:10:51,544
(Under the scorching sun,)

1616
01:10:54,054 --> 01:10:56,684
(Agungi is covered with fiery hot posters.)

1617
01:10:57,084 --> 01:11:00,224
(Smoke rising from the cauldrons)

1618
01:11:00,324 --> 01:11:02,393
(And it leads to the sales...)

1619
01:11:02,394 --> 01:11:05,364
(of 47 dollars.)

1620
01:11:06,064 --> 01:11:08,764
If we sell it cheap, we won't have enough ingredients?

1621
01:11:08,934 --> 01:11:10,804
Even if we lower the price, we can only do it by about a dollar.

1622
01:11:11,204 --> 01:11:13,404
Only then we can make a profit.

1623
01:11:13,574 --> 01:11:15,403
I think they just view it as regular tteokbokki.

1624
01:11:15,404 --> 01:11:18,444
I think they think the prices are too high for tteokbokki.

1625
01:11:19,774 --> 01:11:21,344
We can't keep selling it like this.

1626
01:11:21,514 --> 01:11:23,883
I'll lower the prices.

1627
01:11:23,884 --> 01:11:24,914
(He's decided to lower the prices.)

1628
01:11:25,044 --> 01:11:28,054
(Adjusting the prices)

1629
01:11:28,284 --> 01:11:29,684
I changed them to 5 dollars and 6 dollars.

1630
01:11:30,084 --> 01:11:31,224
- Okay.
- They're 5 dollars and 6 dollars.

1631
01:11:31,854 --> 01:11:33,353
- What?
- I think only popular ones...

1632
01:11:33,354 --> 01:11:35,094
Why are the prices different from earlier?

1633
01:11:35,694 --> 01:11:37,094
- It's five dollars now.
- What?

1634
01:11:37,294 --> 01:11:38,493
- Right.
- How much was it earlier?

1635
01:11:38,494 --> 01:11:40,194
They were 7 dollars and 8 dollars each.

1636
01:11:40,664 --> 01:11:42,533
Shouldn't we lodge a complaint about this?

1637
01:11:42,534 --> 01:11:43,804
- Suddenly...
- They just changed it now?

1638
01:11:44,264 --> 01:11:45,733
- I'll just ask them why.
- Okay.

1639
01:11:45,734 --> 01:11:46,974
She's stepping up.

1640
01:11:47,174 --> 01:11:48,844
(Stepping up)

1641
01:11:49,144 --> 01:11:52,414
They were 7 dollars and 8 dollars, but suddenly...

1642
01:11:53,414 --> 01:11:54,473
It's unfair...

1643
01:11:54,474 --> 01:11:56,114
- to lower the price suddenly.
- Someone didn't eat this.

1644
01:11:56,884 --> 01:12:00,054
There's no way it won't sell after we dropped the price.

1645
01:12:00,484 --> 01:12:04,554
(Agungi)

1646
01:12:04,684 --> 01:12:07,394
A one-star rating has occurred.

1647
01:12:07,894 --> 01:12:10,694
The restaurant with one star is Agungi.

1648
01:12:12,664 --> 01:12:13,694
Agungi.

1649
01:12:14,464 --> 01:12:15,504
Is it a good thing?

1650
01:12:19,004 --> 01:12:20,034
Go Seok Hyun.

1651
01:12:21,134 --> 01:12:23,944
This is absolutely critical.

1652
01:12:24,904 --> 01:12:26,514
- This is a real business.
- This is for real.

1653
01:12:27,644 --> 01:12:30,044
They weren't satisfied with the food.

1654
01:12:30,744 --> 01:12:32,214
It's a star raging, not a penalty point, right?

1655
01:12:32,884 --> 01:12:35,254
We got one star. Isn't it a good thing?

1656
01:12:36,084 --> 01:12:37,184
It's a bad thing, right?

1657
01:12:38,554 --> 01:12:40,223
Isn't it a good thing to get one star?

1658
01:12:40,224 --> 01:12:42,494
No. That means we got 1 out of 5 points.

1659
01:12:43,664 --> 01:12:46,334
Our sales were already the lowest anyway,

1660
01:12:46,794 --> 01:12:50,404
and we even got a one-star review.

1661
01:12:50,764 --> 01:12:54,174
I honestly felt like I was crumbling inside.

1662
01:12:55,404 --> 01:12:59,444
(Tasting the food, feeling bitter)

1663
01:13:06,254 --> 01:13:07,314
What do we do?

1664
01:13:07,914 --> 01:13:09,584
We didn't even sell a lot,

1665
01:13:10,154 --> 01:13:11,484
but we got a one-star review.

1666
01:13:13,524 --> 01:13:14,754
We're in big trouble.

1667
01:13:18,494 --> 01:13:20,494
We have the second surviving restaurant...

1668
01:13:20,964 --> 01:13:23,834
of the 1,000 dollar sales race.

1669
01:13:28,674 --> 01:13:30,944
- My gosh. The 2nd survivor.
- The 2nd restaurant to survive.

1670
01:13:32,274 --> 01:13:34,174
The second restaurant...

1671
01:13:34,974 --> 01:13:37,014
to survive is...

1672
01:13:38,784 --> 01:13:40,013
Bol A Bol.

1673
01:13:40,014 --> 01:13:41,384
(2nd place: Bol A Bol)

1674
01:13:48,224 --> 01:13:50,464
Isn't it the restaurant with Chef Lim Ki Hak?

1675
01:13:50,864 --> 01:13:52,094
This is totally unexpected.

1676
01:13:52,834 --> 01:13:55,604
It's interesting that Chef Ki Hak survived. It's Western cuisine.

1677
01:13:55,904 --> 01:13:57,064
Gosh, Bol A Bol.

1678
01:13:57,464 --> 01:13:59,504
The Western restaurants are doing well.

1679
01:14:00,374 --> 01:14:01,974
I'm feeling so happy.

1680
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:06,974
- This is French cuisine, right?
- Sure.

1681
01:14:08,814 --> 01:14:09,914
Well done.

1682
01:14:11,214 --> 01:14:14,854
Chef Lim Ki Hak definitely has his secret weapon.

1683
01:14:14,954 --> 01:14:17,754
French cuisine works.

1684
01:14:17,984 --> 01:14:20,524
I guess we're just too slow to make it.

1685
01:14:20,924 --> 01:14:23,524
We handled incoming orders without physical order sheets.

1686
01:14:23,624 --> 01:14:25,063
You can't do that unless there's mutual trust.

1687
01:14:25,064 --> 01:14:26,534
Exactly.

1688
01:14:27,034 --> 01:14:28,093
It's all about trust.

1689
01:14:28,094 --> 01:14:30,064
- We just went by what we heard.
- Of course, I trust you.

1690
01:14:31,064 --> 01:14:32,103
I reached my hand out,

1691
01:14:32,104 --> 01:14:34,104
and what I needed was already placed in my hand.

1692
01:14:34,904 --> 01:14:35,974
Spatula.

1693
01:14:37,144 --> 01:14:40,214
My hands are free right now, so I'll prep the chicken for you.

1694
01:14:40,474 --> 01:14:43,714
I'll get the next desserts ready before we run out of this.

1695
01:14:44,044 --> 01:14:45,714
Anyone who has worked in a kitchen...

1696
01:14:45,884 --> 01:14:48,984
will probably relate to what this feels like.

1697
01:14:49,784 --> 01:14:51,454
The process of figuring things out...

1698
01:14:51,624 --> 01:14:53,824
when you're stuck in the middle was the fun part.

1699
01:14:54,494 --> 01:14:56,064
It was really fun.

1700
01:14:56,364 --> 01:14:57,393
Yes.

1701
01:14:57,394 --> 01:15:00,164
(2nd place: Bol A Bol with 1,001.63 dollars in sales)

1702
01:15:03,404 --> 01:15:06,574
The lunch service will be ending shortly.

1703
01:15:07,304 --> 01:15:08,874
Ten, nine,

1704
01:15:09,304 --> 01:15:10,904
eight, seven,

1705
01:15:11,344 --> 01:15:12,944
six, five,

1706
01:15:13,414 --> 01:15:14,944
four, three,

1707
01:15:15,314 --> 01:15:16,844
two, one.

1708
01:15:18,414 --> 01:15:21,114
The lunch service is over.

1709
01:15:22,184 --> 01:15:23,784
- Good work.
- Good work.

1710
01:15:24,884 --> 01:15:26,024
It was so close.

1711
01:15:26,854 --> 01:15:28,694
We will now release...

1712
01:15:28,964 --> 01:15:32,034
the lunch business ranks.

1713
01:15:32,134 --> 01:15:34,064
First place, The Sauce.

1714
01:15:34,364 --> 01:15:36,234
Nice!

1715
01:15:36,364 --> 01:15:37,433
Isn't that amazing?

1716
01:15:37,434 --> 01:15:39,803
(1st place with the total sales of 1,185 dollars)

1717
01:15:39,804 --> 01:15:41,933
Second place, Bol A Bol.

1718
01:15:41,934 --> 01:15:45,443
(2nd place with the total sales of 1,001.63 dollars)

1719
01:15:45,444 --> 01:15:47,843
Third place, The Star In My Heart.

1720
01:15:47,844 --> 01:15:49,013
(Lunch sales)

1721
01:15:49,014 --> 01:15:52,153
(3rd place with 825.83 dollars, 4th place with 626.50 dollars)

1722
01:15:52,154 --> 01:15:55,153
(5th place with 609.52 dollars, 6th place with 594.54 dollars)

1723
01:15:55,154 --> 01:15:57,323
Now, it's time for a break.

1724
01:15:57,324 --> 01:15:58,624
(Time for a break)

1725
01:15:58,894 --> 01:16:02,024
Eighteen teams that didn't sell over a thousand dollars...

1726
01:16:02,664 --> 01:16:05,324
will continue to open for dinner.

1727
01:16:05,434 --> 01:16:06,693
(Sighing)

1728
01:16:06,694 --> 01:16:08,494
- That's cruel.
- That's cruel.

1729
01:16:09,304 --> 01:16:12,504
The bottom 2 teams in Round 1...

1730
01:16:13,904 --> 01:16:15,074
will be closed.

1731
01:16:16,874 --> 01:16:17,904
"Closed."

1732
01:16:18,304 --> 01:16:19,314
Gosh.

1733
01:16:19,614 --> 01:16:21,144
That's the word I hate the most.

1734
01:16:22,014 --> 01:16:23,414
"Closed" is a scary word.

1735
01:16:24,214 --> 01:16:25,314
It's a harsh world.

1736
01:16:25,914 --> 01:16:27,383
For dinner,

1737
01:16:27,384 --> 01:16:29,754
you may add or change your menu items.

1738
01:16:30,254 --> 01:16:31,784
Yes, chef. Understood.

1739
01:16:32,254 --> 01:16:33,624
We must stay alert.

1740
01:16:33,894 --> 01:16:35,564
The difference is only 10 or 20 dollars.

1741
01:16:35,764 --> 01:16:38,294
I bet all the bottom teams are changing their menu items.

1742
01:16:38,734 --> 01:16:40,834
Put your apron on. We're entering battle mode.

1743
01:16:41,894 --> 01:16:43,364
Honestly, we need to make the upper rank.

1744
01:16:44,364 --> 01:16:47,433
(BokBok)

1745
01:16:47,434 --> 01:16:48,434
(Sighing)

1746
01:16:50,504 --> 01:16:52,043
You fool.

1747
01:16:52,044 --> 01:16:53,613
Why couldn't you sell 1,000 dollars?

1748
01:16:53,614 --> 01:16:55,884
And make me work for dinner?

1749
01:16:56,014 --> 01:16:57,014
- Gosh.
- Gosh.

1750
01:16:57,584 --> 01:16:58,814
We'll have to work hard.

1751
01:17:01,814 --> 01:17:03,323
People who are changing the menu items...

1752
01:17:03,324 --> 01:17:05,184
are probably crazy busy right now.

1753
01:17:05,924 --> 01:17:07,754
Do you want to visit Yoo Bang Nyeong?

1754
01:17:08,154 --> 01:17:09,324
See if he's changing it?

1755
01:17:09,794 --> 01:17:10,924
You should go.

1756
01:17:11,564 --> 01:17:13,234
(Yoo Bang Nyeong's Sunlin, 18th place)

1757
01:17:13,794 --> 01:17:15,094
Are you changing the menu?

1758
01:17:15,334 --> 01:17:16,903
- No.
- No?

1759
01:17:16,904 --> 01:17:19,333
- We have a lot of ingredients left.
- We only adjusted the price.

1760
01:17:19,334 --> 01:17:20,733
- We only adjusted the price.
- You did?

1761
01:17:20,734 --> 01:17:21,833
How? Did you raise it?

1762
01:17:21,834 --> 01:17:22,904
Yes, we raised it.

1763
01:17:23,574 --> 01:17:25,944
Because we placed 18th.

1764
01:17:26,414 --> 01:17:28,643
- You placed 18th?
- Yes.

1765
01:17:28,644 --> 01:17:29,843
(I see.)

1766
01:17:29,844 --> 01:17:32,614
If you changed anything, give me a recipe.

1767
01:17:32,854 --> 01:17:33,914
So we can change it.

1768
01:17:34,284 --> 01:17:35,584
I didn't change it.

1769
01:17:36,684 --> 01:17:37,983
It's all or nothing now.

1770
01:17:37,984 --> 01:17:39,023
- Really?
- Yes.

1771
01:17:39,024 --> 01:17:40,654
- If not, we're going home.
- Right.

1772
01:17:41,354 --> 01:17:43,324
We still need to sell everything.

1773
01:17:45,634 --> 01:17:47,094
Good luck.

1774
01:17:47,294 --> 01:17:48,463
- Good luck.
- Bye.

1775
01:17:48,464 --> 01:17:49,504
(Good luck.)

1776
01:17:50,204 --> 01:17:52,603
(After Yeon Bok leaves...)

1777
01:17:52,604 --> 01:17:54,304
- Dad, is this...
- Are you done?

1778
01:17:55,434 --> 01:17:56,674
I'm done.

1779
01:17:57,574 --> 01:18:00,173
Then why don't you fry it...

1780
01:18:00,174 --> 01:18:01,444
- Let's fry it a little.
- Yes.

1781
01:18:02,014 --> 01:18:05,113
If you fry it a little in low heat, it's faster.

1782
01:18:05,114 --> 01:18:06,283
(Talking about their new dinner menu in secret)

1783
01:18:06,284 --> 01:18:07,354
It's easier.

1784
01:18:09,854 --> 01:18:11,523
Did you change the menu or are you staying the same?

1785
01:18:11,524 --> 01:18:12,524
It's the same.

1786
01:18:12,525 --> 01:18:14,024
But we're changing the look.

1787
01:18:14,094 --> 01:18:15,894
We're going to build it up.

1788
01:18:16,224 --> 01:18:17,894
And it's cold at night,

1789
01:18:18,294 --> 01:18:19,734
so we'll give more soup.

1790
01:18:20,064 --> 01:18:22,534
Oh, should I make a combo too?

1791
01:18:23,804 --> 01:18:25,333
It's Chef Edward Kwon.

1792
01:18:25,334 --> 01:18:26,933
Why are you all coming here?

1793
01:18:26,934 --> 01:18:28,834
- What's your place?
- Eleventh.

1794
01:18:29,004 --> 01:18:30,844
That's still safe.

1795
01:18:31,044 --> 01:18:33,143
My strategy totally failed.

1796
01:18:33,144 --> 01:18:35,343
- I expected the office workers...
- Right.

1797
01:18:35,344 --> 01:18:37,584
- to drink last night, - Gukbap or...

1798
01:18:37,614 --> 01:18:38,843
- and in the daytime, - soup.

1799
01:18:38,844 --> 01:18:40,553
they'd look for something to relieve their hangover.

1800
01:18:40,554 --> 01:18:42,013
So I insisted on adding jjamppong.

1801
01:18:42,014 --> 01:18:44,284
That's why I added jjamppong, but it wasn't popular.

1802
01:18:44,484 --> 01:18:46,224
You know what I realised today?

1803
01:18:46,724 --> 01:18:48,554
I still have a long way to go.

1804
01:18:48,694 --> 01:18:50,323
I analysed.

1805
01:18:50,324 --> 01:18:52,163
I even used AI...

1806
01:18:52,164 --> 01:18:53,964
- to look up.
- You even used AI?

1807
01:18:54,134 --> 01:18:55,833
